(1, 'Sealed Fate', 'uploads/1/game.jpg', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'Imagine a text adventure where you have to traverse a tunnel of caves with only a baby for light. Spooky!', 'uploads/1/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Mat', 'CC BY', 'Other', 15286, 3041, '2012-03-31 01:52:14', '2012-04-01 02:51:36', '1984ce4cbc46da2d547f511b97b1f21a'),
(2, 'Every Night I Dream I''m Better', 'uploads/2/game.png', 'Visualize an open world game set in a white box. During the night you dream and can place elements from your dream into the blank world', 'A boy in a hospital room dreams of adventure in a video game world...', 'http://dev.gritfish.net/molyjam/', '', 'Sydney, Australia', '', 'John Kane\r\nMatt Hamm', 'CC BY', 'Other', 7024, 1239, '2012-03-31 21:06:06', '2012-03-31 21:07:15', '273be06b413a7f9a5b0f2b7dad0aabd6'),
(3, 'Hush, sun, hush', 'uploads/3/game.png', 'What if your son was the sun? If he sleeps, the sun vanishes. If he cries then woodlands set on fire etc', 'Hush, sun, hush is a massively multiplayer rhythm game. Work together with other worshippers around the world to sooth the sun to sleep.\r\n \r\nMake a shushing pattern, and then repeat it over and over to sooth the baby. It works even better if you match rhythms with the other players. Play with headphones and zone out to the soothing sounds of the wind and waves.', 'http://hushsunhush.com', 'http://youtu.be/wf3buzgFGKY', 'Internet', 'uploads/3/team.jpg', 'Bo (and Alisa) Brinkman', 'CC BY', 'None', 3012, 357, '2012-03-31 21:11:39', '2012-04-02 05:39:10', '6312252a2ba8a97cbf737f5b516ad790'),
(4, 'Super Mystical Bunny', 'uploads/4/game.png', 'You control a mystical rabbit at a bus stop during Winter. You must find as many creative ways as possible to make people miss their buses.', 'A text based spinning-plates style game. Written with JavaScript. Play it in your browser!\r\n<p>\r\nBuilt over an afternoon while watching the other MollyJam ChCh teams work :)</p>', 'http://nelsont.x10.mx/BunnyGame/Start.html', '', 'Christchurch, New Zealand', 'uploads/4/team.jpg', 'Tek', 'CC BY', 'None', 7369, 1739, '2012-03-31 22:03:40', '2012-04-01 03:21:36', '376074853cd62dafcae6410a2e6d2ac0'),
(5, 'ITALIAN ROCKET RIDERS', 'uploads/5/game.png', 'Racing game where you only have 2 speeds. 0MPH and 10,000 MPH.\r\nDid you just run over a little child? \r\nwho knows? how does that make you feel?', 'Two player racing game where there are only 2 speeds: Stop and Go. Try not to run anyone over.\r\n\r\nhttps://twitter.com/#!/JigxorAndy', 'uploads/5/game.zip', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'Andrew Sum (@JigxorAndy)', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 12106, 3952, '2012-03-31 23:29:12', '2012-04-01 00:50:03', 'b4a87a88c328a0608c8da500a0caf3ae'),
(6, 'Apocalypse Grandpa: Geriatric Overload', 'uploads/6/game.jpg', 'What if your 99 year old grandfather was a key? Would you force him to travel across the world just to open a secret door?', 'Right-to-left side-scrolling action platformer with truly emotional gameplay.', 'http://db.tt/GcAu8PxK', '', 'Phoenix, USA', '', '2D Art:\r\n\r\nRyan Ellis\r\nDalton Hefner\r\nZachary Snader\r\n\r\n3D Art:\r\n\r\nAlex Rodriguez\r\n\r\nProgramming:\r\n\r\nTommy Turner\r\n\r\nProgramming Novice:\r\n\r\nZachary Snader\r\n\r\nDesign:\r\n\r\nZachary Snader\r\nAlex Rodriguez\r\n\r\nMenus:\r\n\r\nZachary Snader\r\n\r\nMusic and Sound:\r\n\r\nZachary Snader\r\nAndrew Kroepel\r\n\r\nSpecial thanks to everyone else that helped!', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 2802, 563, '2012-03-31 23:29:33', '2012-04-02 20:49:32', '5b9ca887aafb3dd3da22fd467f640863'),
(202, 'What Would Molydeux?', 'uploads/202/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time', 'A card game where players create sentences using cards which contain words and phrases from @PeterMolydeux''s twitter feed, playing their full stops to complete the sentence and score points.\r\n\r\nThe link is to a ~40MB archive containing the PNGs for the deck as well as the scripts used to build it.\r\n\r\nIt can (soon) be printed by Game Crafter on real playing cards.  The price will be whatever their cost of printing is.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.thegamecrafter.com/games/what-would-molydeux-partial-deck', 'uploads/202/game.zip', '', 'NYC, USA', '', 'Jeremy Neiman, Andy Zickler, Alex Coulombe, Sam Kaplan', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 172, 18, '2012-04-01 21:46:50', '2012-04-02 07:13:13', 'd7376be8b37aa2430e68493001b0d6ad'),
(8, 'The Miner', 'uploads/8/game.png', 'Imagine a world where people don''t talk, physical words are hidden underground. You must travel the world hunting ''I'', ''love'' and ''you.', 'You are a miner.\r\nThere is a girl.\r\nYou don''t know what to say to her.\r\nDig for things that will brighten up her day.', 'uploads/8/game.zip', '', 'Sydney, Australia', '', 'Dougy', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameMaker', 2066, 397, '2012-03-31 23:58:58', '2012-04-01 00:32:46', '27eb832cb58117a9b5fccc2d654a2a47'),
(9, 'A Period Piece', 'uploads/9/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time', 'Wilbert Wykeham-Fuller, the punctuated protagonist and periodic pugilist with a propensity for providing powerful punches to the perfunctory pushovers populating this player propelled package, promises punishment for people who do not participate. \r\n\r\nWilbert wants to terminate clauses, but not every clause requires his attention. Help him tell the difference between the spots that are hot and those are not by clicking in the correct places.\r\n\r\nPress the full stop key to proceed', 'uploads/9/game.zip', '', 'Adelaide, Australia', '', 'Jaime von Schwarzburg @tmthesaurus,\r\nJoshua Douglass-Molloy @thejoshdm,\r\nColin Capurso,\r\nSaxon Douglass', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 2189, 462, '2012-04-01 00:29:21', '2012-04-01 21:50:05', '75cf10a5bb6f10fe2427fdfa94d1b7b1'),
(10, 'Days of Your', 'uploads/10/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time.', 'Press the appropriate punctuation character at the correct time to progress.\r\n\r\nFor some reason it crashes to desktop when loading the fonts, so I took out the text. It''s still playable, just a lot harder. Watch the video if you need hints on what to do. \r\n\r\nI''ve only done a Windows build, although it''s written using Made With Marmalade, so in theory most platforms (including mobile) are doable. If there''s a huge demand for it I''ll look into other platforms and fixing up the fonts.', 'uploads/10/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tWHLduxCu24&feature=youtu.be', 'Sydney, Australia', '', 'Chris Glover @mad_maw', 'CC BY', 'None', 863, 47, '2012-04-01 01:09:44', '2012-04-01 19:04:27', '023987a8be60f504dec22e2675d26fe7'),
(11, 'Puppenhaus', 'uploads/11/game.png', 'https://twitter.com/#!/petermolydeux/status/16461096043 - Would love to make a world war 2 game where you control a child who makes his own weapons and traps like the boy in Home Alone.', 'Defend you radio from enemy soldiers using your childish creativity and conveniently placed household objects.\r\n\r\nNOTE: Game was not completed, and so AI bugs out.', 'http://www.rantbox.com.au/games/Puppenhaus/Puppenhaus_Game.html', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HD4p5ayq7ps&feature=youtu.be', 'Melbourne, Australia', 'uploads/11/team.jpg', 'Guy Nobel - Sound; Dan Clayton - Everything Else', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Unity3D', 1247, 164, '2012-04-01 01:31:07', '2012-04-02 02:54:33', 'a6f6c36d894f137e03802d4d564efafd'),
(12, 'Still Life', 'uploads/12/game.jpg', 'Imagine controlling a tear, similar to flower but instead of fields you navigate a naked body.', 'A Mannequin, A Tear, and their memories. - Use mouse to aim movement, left click to jump, right click to zoom out. Collect the 5 memory bubbles.', 'http://www.villavanilla.com/temp/sl/StillLife.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HM8LWjbcRp4', 'Sydney, Australia', 'uploads/12/team.png', 'Zaraar Khattak\r\nHee-eun Yeo\r\nCuauhtemoc "oddgoo" Moreno', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 1784, 393, '2012-04-01 01:37:18', '2012-04-03 07:45:05', '526f83e49171f297ad0281c38977e2d9'),
(13, 'Bowling for Zombieland', 'uploads/13/game.png', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'A town filled with zombies, multiplayer, PvE/PvP, bowl to kill zombies and other players, sign in with FB (get avatar in game), save a frightened cold pixel in the middle of the city and bring it to safety and get points. We had alot of plans, but not enough time/strength to do it. We choose to be "hardcore" and program the game in JavaScript/HTML5. It might only work on Firefox.\r\nhttp://www.killgame.se/', 'http://www.killgame.se/', '', 'Malmö, Sweden', 'uploads/13/team.png', 'James Newnorth - Programming,\r\nFabian Jakobsson - Graphics', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'None', 4767, 2381, '2012-04-01 01:47:27', '2012-04-01 01:51:06', '1c71a33100b99ba243214746e9aaa0c7'),
(14, 'Marco', 'uploads/14/game.png', 'FPS War game, you control the teddy bear of a child who has just escaped a death camp. Help them find their mother using your wits', 'You are wandering the streets looking for your mother. She calls to you from afar - find her.', 'http://danieljeffery.net/sites/default/files/GameFiles/Marco/Marco.html', '', 'Sydney, Australia', '', 'Daniel Jeffery\r\nWade Clarke\r\nWill Algar\r\nMichal Chu', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 957, 187, '2012-04-01 01:57:41', '2012-04-02 05:46:43', '6440bc37db1dad5327e16752c5f485f5'),
(15, 'Hunger Quake', 'uploads/15/game.png', 'What if your tummy rumbling created earthquakes? In a world where food is rare.', 'Jump using SPACEBAR.\r\nCollect FOOD to stay ALIVE.\r\n\r\nMade in under 20 hours!', 'uploads/15/game.zip', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', 'uploads/15/team.jpg', 'Art & Design: Chad Toprak (chadtoprak@gmail.com, @MrCh4d)\r\nDesign & Code: Ho Hsin Yang (hamsteyr@gmail.com)', 'CC BY-ND', 'Unity3D', 1553, 302, '2012-04-01 02:01:09', '2012-04-02 14:25:43', 'cba3ad2facb3978836ff1fc42c6341de'),
(16, 'You Are A Spy & The World Is Transparent', 'uploads/16/game.png', 'Imagine being a spy in a game world where the entire environment is transparent and so you can''t hide. -- https://twitter.com/#!/petermolydeux/status/25248670618230785', 'This game was intended to be played with minimal instructions. You can plant surveillance devices. </br></br>\r\n\r\nPlease play the downloadable version if possible. The mac version is at http://www.toeofdoom.com/YouAreASpy/YouAreASpy_OSX.zip and the web version is at http://www.toeofdoom.com/YouAreASpy/ </br></br>\r\n\r\nIf you are interested the source is at http://www.toeofdoom.com/YouAreASpy/YouAreASpySource.zip ', 'http://www.toeofdoom.com/YouAreASpy/YouAreASpy_Win32.zip', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'Matthew Elvey Price (@Toeofdoom) - Programming and stuff</br>\r\nChad Toprak (@MrCh4d) - Art (Character & Animation)', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 2487, 575, '2012-04-01 02:05:56', '2012-04-03 05:41:41', 'e246eb420ec44c2564fc95dbd3925337'),
(17, 'Devil May Cry', 'uploads/17/game.png', 'World is being taken over by demons, you play as a human disguised as the demon psychologist of the demon leader.', '[The] world is being taken over by demons, you play as a human disguised as the demon psychologist of the demon leader.', 'uploads/17/game.zip', '', 'Sydney, Australia', 'uploads/17/team.jpg', 'RC - everything but the ticking clock sound\r\nandriala (freesound.org) - ticking clock sound', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 1619, 244, '2012-04-01 02:18:07', '2012-04-01 02:18:07', 'f324064d06b466bbd672856ce85a49ef'),
(18, 'Pigeon Quest', 'uploads/18/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'Pick up the items to make business men and women not kill themselves while dodging increasing numbers of hawks and pots.', 'uploads/18/game.zip', '', 'Adelaide, Australia', '', 'Robert Reed\r\nColin Capurso', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'GameMaker', 1113, 223, '2012-04-01 02:19:23', '2012-04-01 02:39:08', 'cbefa447bbf367dd938bbfe3e3706764'),
(19, 'Old Man Babby', 'uploads/19/game.png', 'You grow from baby to old man and back to baby and this keeps looping every 10 seconds. Small gap? Time it so you can go through as a baby.', 'Play back and forth through your past and future with Old Man Babby.', 'uploads/19/game.zip', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'Andrew Brophy, \r\nJames Rhodes, \r\nGuy Noble, \r\nMatt Parsons', 'CC BY', 'XNA', 928, 182, '2012-04-01 02:20:09', '2012-04-01 04:10:48', 'a62d4a4d45d3a30dcaa43791d3dbaabd'),
(24, 'Don''t Deux It', 'uploads/24/game.png', 'You are a pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'Exactly as the tweet dictates. Embraced the emotional adventure game hidden in that tweet. ;)\r\n\r\nAlso used another Molydeux tweet as wisdom... "Less numbers, more emotion."\r\n\r\nFind the jumpers, cure their woes. ', 'http://johnsietsma.org/site_media/DontDeuxIt.html', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'John Sietsma (@johnsietsma), Trent Kusters (@trentkusters), Simon Boxer (@sboxle), Guy Noble (@thenobleguy)', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 4252, 989, '2012-04-01 02:41:01', '2012-04-01 08:11:28', '7d255f7eea0e0048d7cd9620da0a8dd6'),
(20, 'mirror', 'uploads/20/game.png', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors? Could add more depth by having dirty mirrors that need to be cleaned?', 'Collect all of the dots without running into a ghost!', 'uploads/20/game.zip', 'http://youtu.be/RtDzV8Sso2k', 'Adelaide, Australia', 'uploads/20/team.png', 'Saxon Douglass', 'CC BY', 'None', 586, 95, '2012-04-01 02:22:23', '2012-04-02 02:01:35', '5204af4da0b5060632bbf37f23ad2e25'),
(21, 'I Hate Romans', 'uploads/21/game.png', 'Why are there always MASSIVE monster ''bosses'' in modern games? Would it not be so refreshing to have to fight a very cunning ant?', 'http://www.stickymill.com/cyclops\r\n\r\nDefend yourself and block the Romans attacks with your mouse', 'http://www.stickymill.com/cyclops', '', 'Adelaide, Australia', '', 'Colin Capurso\r\nChristopher Johnson', 'CC BY', 'None', 1322, 270, '2012-04-01 02:26:29', '2012-04-01 02:27:00', '1f6b38afa0e1858a8d8d887ba94bcaf2'),
(22, 'The Spandex Parable', 'uploads/22/game.png', 'You know, what if the aim of the game was to resist actually completing it? That kept me up all night yesterday. ', 'At the end of this game is the most lewd, gratuitous sex scene you''ll ever see in a video game. The developers spent most of their time making it as salacious and graphic as possible. None of this Bioware stuff-- where you don''t get to see anything, and you have awkward animation clipping-- no. This will be the real deal. Oh, I can''t wait! ', 'uploads/22/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UkdZ8WGf6is', 'Adelaide, Australia', 'uploads/22/team.png', 'Chris Johnson(@HyperNexus), Sam Crisp(@Sam_Crisp), Matt Trobbiani(@Orann), Jan Bielecki(@Disco_box), Colin Capurso(@colincapurso). Music from Kevin Macleod', 'CC BY', 'Other', 3608, 1795, '2012-04-01 02:28:15', '2012-04-04 01:57:42', '0de838da371e0373aa665bc7c6664f28'),
(23, 'Paused', 'uploads/23/game.jpg', 'What if the pause button was a weapon? Until developers think outside the box we''re going downhill.', 'Welcome to same-keyboard multiplayer gaming that publishers are too shortsighted to bring you. Introducing the Pause Pickup. Don’t like the lay of the land? Cowardly opponent cowering behind their coward wall? Pause, swap the level mid-game, resume. Where’s your cover now, huh? Finally, the pause button is your greatest weapon. Use it wisely.', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/19971570/Paused/Paused.html', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'Rhys van der Waerden,\r\nNed Charles Kirner', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 839, 185, '2012-04-01 02:28:18', '2012-04-02 09:54:27', 'f50e05ebe882bcfcc9a3df5809140554'),
(25, 'Gap', 'uploads/25/game.png', 'Your child is made of lego, you have to detatch bricks to make bridges etc You need to keep adding bricks to stop him getting depressed.', 'Build bridges out of your child''s memories.', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/38227417/WebPlayer/WebPlayer.html', '', 'Melbourne, Australia', '', 'Justin Whitfort, Tim Mutton, Joshua Bradbury, Rebecca Knight, Matthew Parsons, Shelley Du', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 832, 169, '2012-04-01 02:49:54', '2012-04-01 07:54:32', '9bfdf9e253f74b9a769adcc8deea9475'),
(30, 'Reflections', 'uploads/30/game.png', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors? Could add more depth by having dirty mirrors that need to be cleaned?', 'At the moment, an extremely simple and mostly-functional interactive raytracer, including objects that can only be seen in reflections. Does that count as a game? I think Molydeux would count it.\r\n\r\nESC to quit, wasd to move, mouse to look.\r\n\r\nIf you don''t like 1600x900 resolution, you will have to recompile the game.', 'uploads/30/game.zip', '', 'Adelaide, Australia', 'uploads/30/team.jpg', 'James Picone', 'CC BY', 'None', 567, 108, '2012-04-01 07:41:27', '2012-04-01 07:41:28', '7c3bc5cba3d9792b16f4f3907073c706'),
(27, 'Rat Wrangler', 'uploads/27/game.png', 'Imagine if when you kill someone their death animation loops and ''burns'' into your screen so you have to watch it for the rest of the game?', 'http://oddfinch.com/molydeux/\r\n(should work well in Chrome or Safari)\r\nKill rats to build up a burned-in wall of corpses and use them to herd their living brethren into the missing block design. Celebrate your success.', 'http://oddfinch.com/molydeux/', '', 'Internet', '', 'Alan Joyce (GB: thisisalan)', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 459, 62, '2012-04-01 04:25:08', '2012-04-01 15:30:34', '5d5933d2fff8517bc6f2a4a3a01f5f22'),
(28, 'The Loor is Fava', 'uploads/28/game.png', 'A game where if you touch the floor you die. The only way to progress is to kill enemies and use their bodies as platforms.', 'Your father has had a worsining alcoholism problem for many years. It''s gotten so bad that he''s started spewing up blood everywhere. Watch out for his inner demons and ghosts that are after you. Find your mother at the beacon in the distance she''ll look after you.', 'uploads/28/game.zip', '', 'Christchurch, New Zealand', 'uploads/28/team.jpg', 'Kasper Brown\r\nSimon Frost', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 903, 133, '2012-04-01 04:55:17', '2012-04-01 04:55:17', '399bb612d2c891cead16a57210c70467'),
(29, 'My Last Friend', 'uploads/29/game.png', 'You''re a scarecrow in a world with just 1 bird', 'Love your new last friend. Will you be able to keep him with you forever?\r\n\r\nIt takes 2 minutes, it''s strange and it''s about sharing love\r\n\r\n"Ok. I saw it. Found it dumb. Sorry. I''d recommend that you put a little more time in your work and be a little more sincere." [Tale of Tales]', 'uploads/29/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gqhzQ-6niEs&hd=1', 'Utrecht, Netherlands', '', 'Alex Camilleri\r\n@SnakeEaterITA\r\nwww.alexcamilleri.com', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameMaker', 1371, 250, '2012-04-01 06:02:29', '2012-04-02 21:53:42', '918eaae0f73234b8fb8a05d8b7c468ce'),
(31, 'Imagine', 'uploads/31/game.png', '"Try to imagine a game in which you have an imaginary friend who doesn''t believe you are real, you must convince them that you are."', 'Can you help a little boy deal with his issues or will he simply dream?', 'uploads/31/game.zip', 'http://youtu.be/AM_bcoCX-ak', 'Brighton, UK', 'uploads/31/team.jpg', 'Michael O''Hare', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 443, 59, '2012-04-01 08:27:18', '2012-04-01 11:37:08', '241e6573db9a8555fb3e36ab9eedd1de'),
(32, 'Bear Survival', 'uploads/32/game.png', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors? Could add more depth by having dirty mirrors that need to be cleaned?', 'You and your bear lady have decided to explore a nearby haunted meadow, but before you even realize what has happened, she is spirited away by ghosts. You must make it alive to the other end of the meadow to save her. The ghosts in the meadow can only been seen through the magical mirrors littered across the meadow. You are not alone with the ghosts in the meadow however...', 'uploads/32/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Heikki Tormala', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 715, 110, '2012-04-01 08:44:00', '2012-04-01 09:17:44', '230dd25948c89d9b034dd2d0ebdb7e58'),
(33, '...?...!', 'uploads/33/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time.', '"Grammar Hero": add punctuation to classic texts or THE WORLD WILL BE DESTROYED. http://people.csail.mit.edu/owenm/molyjam2012/', 'http://people.csail.mit.edu/owenm/molyjam2012/', '', 'Boston, USA', 'uploads/33/team.jpg', 'Naomi Hinchen, Owen Macindoe, Dean Tate, Anthony Castiglia', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 683, 117, '2012-04-01 09:06:19', '2012-04-01 09:06:19', '83a14aa806bc8d37db00c9b0405d7921'),
(34, 'Ghost Horror', 'uploads/34/game.jpg', 'You live in a little house made of guns. You need many guns to fight invaders but you also need to keep a roof on top of your many children.', 'You are trapped in a remote logging house. You must survive by any means.\r\n\r\nUse the flashlight to fry ghosts(Left mouse).\r\nRight mouse click and hold to pick up objects to create cover.', 'uploads/34/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ysFpyJ6davo&feature=channel', 'Internet', 'uploads/34/team.jpg', 'Max Ko\r\nLina', 'CC BY-SA', 'Unity3D', 863, 138, '2012-04-01 09:13:35', '2012-04-01 18:08:59', 'a78bcadbf9c80aa41258dd6cfa90c650'),
(288, 'Loonie', 'uploads/288/game.png', 'Game where are a coin being passed around. Must travel as far as possible, placing yourself in ideal places to be picked up and transported', 'The start of a hypertext fiction story about different people who discover a coin that ties together shared experiences. ', 'uploads/288/game.zip', '', 'Montreal, Canada', '', '@Seemo', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 7, 3, '2012-04-03 18:30:32', '2012-04-03 18:32:00', '5712926a9c9e017702e559100671cb57'),
(35, '1000 milliseconds', 'uploads/35/game.png', 'Perhaps someone could make the game that never was? A game that lasts one second?', 'You have exactly one second to click anywhere on the screen once click the play button. Then depending on where you clicked you will be shown a picture for a second. That picture is one of the 100 clues. And you can only play this game "once". The pictures have a certain main and sub sequence. Each of the main sequences unravel a word. And word by word you must figure out the final message which is one of Peter Molydeux''s tweets. Facebook group and twitter: 1000milliseconds (add # for twitter)', 'http://vimarshraina.com/game/', '', 'Dundee, UK', 'uploads/35/team.jpg', 'Vimarsh Raina', 'CC BY', 'None', 684, 111, '2012-04-01 09:20:16', '2012-04-01 09:27:36', '4929b7690eb7a17b6a961257d1a1886c'),
(36, 'Zâmbeşti', 'uploads/36/game.png', 'Imagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other. You on the other hand, your only ability is to hug those around you.', 'You play as Nina, a girl who is determined to change the world by hugging everyone she meets.\r\n\r\nThe game can be played over the Internet.\r\n\r\nA game made in Copenhagen, Denmark by a game developer from Malta.', 'http://scutajar.com/files/games/zambesti/index.html', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/36/team.jpg', 'Simon Cutajar (@scutajar) - Programming, Art, Music, Sound Effects', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 264, 38, '2012-04-01 09:34:11', '2012-04-02 16:17:10', '61a485e669ff20b0ae82198c983dadac'),
