(42, 'Pro Business Simulator ', 'uploads/42/game.png', '"You are a pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home."', 'Our game further explores the concept raised above and asks the questions: What is the businessman''s story? What if there was no pigeon? Or, even worse, what if the pigeon was a business competitor?\r\n\r\nType verbs to motivate your coworkers. Take part in deadly jargon battles. Can you meet the third quarter''s sales forecast?', 'http://www.blackshipsfillthesky.com/ProBusiness/WebPlayer.html', '', 'Internet', '', 'Evan Greenwood\r\nRuan Rothmann', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 567, 109, '2012-04-01 10:04:30', '2012-04-01 10:04:30', '6a53c13863e29bf7a7ce18312af7763e'),
(43, 'Hugbot''s interactive lovin''', 'uploads/43/game.png', 'Imagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other. You on the other hand, your only ability is to hug those around you.', 'Hug as many humans as possible before they kill themselves!', 'uploads/43/game.zip', '', 'Brighton, UK', '', 'Carl Bateman - Programming\r\n\r\nAdam Kelly - Programming\r\n\r\nSophie Kinnear - Design / Art\r\n\r\nFrancis Kimberley - Music', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'XNA', 359, 52, '2012-04-01 10:08:48', '2012-04-02 01:56:39', 'a02c3568bb118df5296d25cf04f1960c'),
(44, 'Why do birds suddenly appear?!', 'uploads/44/game.jpg', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'You play a 5 year old pigeon, in 1996 Shanghai. It''s a summer heatwave, and suicide is at an all time high, though the economy is better than ever. Knowing that you haven''t long left in life, you find yourself placed as the only one able to save several individuals from themselves.\r\n\r\nImagine a text based drama where every decision influences the outlook of your character. Not only their body, but their spirit, every action outcome determined both by your choices & your outlook. ', 'uploads/44/game.zip', '', 'Brighton, UK', 'uploads/44/team.jpg', 'Rowan Peet (@ShinAzure) - Scripting/Code\r\nTobias Cooper - Cover Image', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 524, 84, '2012-04-01 10:16:25', '2012-04-02 06:30:17', 'c12590b1aaf8e960b005f185a17247f2'),
(45, 'Dokideux Panikku', 'uploads/45/game.jpg', '"Imagine if your player avatar feared you? became anxious if you press the buttons too hard and fast etc?"', 'The tweet sums up the concept pretty well - it''s a pretty classic platformer with the added twist that if you press the arrows too fast, your character gets more and more nervous, to the point where he''ll stand still, frozen in terror. (That''s typically when you lose). As the character gets more nervous, the screen letterboxes also close in on the center, making it harder to see what''s ahead. Takes a lot of finesse to actually finish the level.', 'http://emmettbutler.com/dokideux/', '', 'Internet', '', 'Emmett Butler - twitter.com/emmett9001 - design/program\r\nDiego Garcia - twitter.com/radstronomical - design/art ', 'CC BY', 'Other', 695, 158, '2012-04-01 10:34:17', '2012-04-01 10:34:18', '948d821ec20e2d4478ba62b9a2c74192'),
