(79, 'Full Stopple', 'uploads/79/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time', 'Full Stopple is a 2D scroller with a twist. You are a full stop. Jump over Spaces with Space. If you think there is supposed to be a period, do not jump to place it.\r\n\r\nThere are currently 2 "stories".\r\n\r\nSince my upload fails, her is the link to download it: http://www.mediafire.com/?r6xoc68x34im6to', 'uploads/79/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Only me, faxilux. :) \r\n', 'CC BY', 'Other', 112, 13, '2012-04-01 14:49:19', '2012-04-02 00:52:00', 'acf9571bdd636e8f1d5bfc849abb9d85'),
(80, 'Vivid Imagination', 'uploads/80/game.png', '"Try to imagine a game in which you have an imaginary friend who doesn’t believe you are real, you must convince them that you are."', 'A short text based dialogue game with  many choices to explore worth replaying a few times to see all of the options. Visit wally2069.blogspot.com for other games made by this designer. ', 'uploads/80/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Jon R Wallace (wally2069)', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameMaker', 153, 26, '2012-04-01 14:49:33', '2012-04-01 14:52:39', 'b705be1e0b08ddfca867c2f18a91395c'),
(81, 'OnADime', 'uploads/81/game.png', 'Imagine playing the only coin in the world and you''re being used to decide on outcomes for all global debates.', 'Code complete for the end of the Jam but not content complete! \r\n\r\nSo the point of the game is you make decisions on government policies. The decisions effect six metrics Gold, School System, Crime level, Armed Forces, Health and Industry. It also keeps track of the groups who like and dislike you.\r\n\r\nAt the moment you cant lose unless you run out of money.\r\n\r\nOnly play if you are REALLY interested. I will put out an updated version before the end of the week.\r\n\r\nControls are left right and space.', 'http://wtapps.blogspot.com/2012/04/molyjam-completed-game.html', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/81/team.png', 'Seamus Ryan and Iho, The shark.', 'CC BY-ND', 'None', 91, 12, '2012-04-01 14:53:33', '2012-04-02 14:23:09', 'dc0104e65ba22abcc24cd2c418fbf05f'),
(82, 'The Bear of Love', 'uploads/82/game.png', 'You are a bear but for some reason your oxygen comes from hugging people. Problem is that hugging people breaks their bones.', 'Spread love through hugs! You''re a forest bear which carries a curse. Your oxygen comes from people''s hug with you, problem is that you''re still a bear and if you hug someone for too long, it''ll be dead in no time. In order to break your curse and make the world a better place, hug the old corporate owner in the center of the city, who has no love in his heart at all. HOW TO PLAY ON README.TXT!', 'uploads/82/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'LeBrancher (Oscar Esgalha), rzafael (Rafael Esgalha)', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 198, 34, '2012-04-01 14:56:16', '2012-04-02 04:15:30', 'efb617ce2e447c06e005964f1de55965'),
(85, 'CuddlePit', '', 'Imagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other.  You on the other hand, your only ability is to hug those around you.', 'Spread kindness, love and cuteness to the denizens of Hell utilizing a caring embrace.  As the only one in Hell capable of hugging, it is your duty to help the demons find happiness.  Left to themselves, they would destroy one-another.  Also, you are a penguin.', 'http://www.ingridcheung.com/cuddlepit/', '', 'Boston, USA', '', 'Programmer, Artist: Morgan Quirk\r\nDesigner: Dan Dujnic\r\nProgrammer, Art Director: Ingrid Cheung\r\nMusic & SFX: Anthony Castiglia\r\nAdditional Audio: Miles Flanagan\r\nTesters:\r\nVarious and many at MolyJam Boston', 'CC BY', 'Other', 245, 60, '2012-04-01 15:16:39', '2012-04-01 15:27:51', '20cc6e0491bee25f3a773fec7bf402a4'),
(86, 'The Crugger', 'uploads/86/game.jpg', 'Imagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other. You on the other hand, your only ability is to hug those around you.', 'The Crugger, a time-survival game where everyone''s mood is dropping really fast... unless YOU, the Gummy-bear, come to hug them !\r\n(the bear idea comes from another Molydeux''s tweet, but I had not time for implementing the rest of it... ^^)\r\n\r\nMade by Bertrand Riché, and as I''m no graphic artist at all, I''ve made what I can for the "art"...\r\nAlso available at http://bertrandriche.fr/external/molyjam/ ', 'http://bertrandriche.fr/external/molyjam', '', 'Montreal, Canada', '', 'Bertrand Riché (@bertrandriche)', 'CC BY', 'None', 104, 16, '2012-04-01 15:17:29', '2012-04-02 06:17:37', '6e692ae97d565aef5dde0942de501cd9'),
(185, 'War Alone', 'uploads/185/game.png', 'I want to make a World War 2 game. What? been done before? No, you see in MY game you don''t control a solider but a 4 year old child.', '(Due to only getting to work on it for a day) this is mostly an interactive storytelling piece demo, also due to constraints introducing as a first the QTI. The actual game would allow the kid to use way more toys, at the end maybe fight hitler or even reunite with his parents?!?', 'http://www.stimunation.com/previews/molydeux2/', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/185/team.jpg', '@Tommosaur', 'CC BY', 'Other', 98, 18, '2012-04-01 20:14:42', '2012-04-01 20:14:43', 'ae7cdce391b972840d7d3e3050be7e86'),
(87, 'Aholeic', 'uploads/87/game.jpg', 'You play a hole, you must move around an environment making certain elements fall into correct targets at the right time.', 'Collect the right cubes with one end and put them in the correct place!', 'uploads/87/game.zip', '', 'Dieburg, Germany', '', 'Marc Kobusch\r\nTobias Kalle\r\nJoanna Almeida', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 112, 18, '2012-04-01 15:17:46', '2012-04-01 15:17:46', '182e27d177d27abe0375f967eeb0f7a4'),
(88, 'Climb a Rope', 'uploads/88/game.jpg', 'Can you visualise a world where horizontal is impossible? You are forever falling or attached to verticals?', 'Flixel game in which you climb a rope! You are down to your last fedora. Can you reach the roof of your building where you left the box of backup hats?', 'uploads/88/game.zip', '', 'Boston, USA', '', 'Brendan Mcloughlin\r\nJonathan Rubinger\r\nChad Serrant\r\nMiles Flanagan\r\nRick Cody', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 248, 52, '2012-04-01 15:18:31', '2012-04-01 20:54:55', '41abe91dbb94c6b975d6de34fe88a45e'),
(192, 'Hannibal and the Dog', 'uploads/192/game.png', 'Game where you control a full stop. Enemies read you stories you and you have to jump in between words at the right time', 'WARNING: NOT on par with other games on the site. Waste time on this game at your own risk. Game was made in two hours using the crappy Mac version of Game Maker Lite, so only playable from the development environment itself.', 'uploads/192/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/192/team.jpg', 'Code, idea, design, art: Victor Breum (@HapZep).\r\nBeta testing: Kirsten Bjergarde, Nikolai Elmore.\r\nFinancing: Brenton Elmore.\r\nInvaluable support: Emil, Euclid, Spirit.', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'GameMaker', 58, 9, '2012-04-01 21:00:26', '2012-04-01 21:06:20', '30501b251c739363acc356a11c327d24'),
(90, 'Molytron', 'uploads/90/game.png', 'You control an entertainment unit in a large family home. You choose their games, music, and films. All of which influence their future.', 'You are the Molytron. You expose a family to movies of your choice, and see the effect on their happiness, sanity, and future!\r\n\r\nIt''s a turn-based family simulator with a unique perspective. Your choice of movies interacts with each family member''s mood, their mood influences what events happen to them, and these events set their mood. Over time, they accumulate or lose long-term happiness, and this determines the ending.', 'uploads/90/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CdgxLvl_kmY', 'Boston, USA', '', 'Matthew Michaud, Michael Hutchinson', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 680, 23, '2012-04-01 15:21:53', '2012-04-02 00:03:29', '99cfa656d38eb4f79371da3da113bf4f'),
(91, 'Escape from Mirror Mansion', 'uploads/91/game.png', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors?', 'You have to escape a haunted house where you can only see the ghosts in the mirrors', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PbdGYPc9oEE', 'Toronto, Canada', '', 'Jamie Whitten\r\nSteve Collins\r\nAndre Fernades', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 165, 0, '2012-04-01 15:23:13', '2012-04-02 17:20:11', '0b613ec88a58acdfaeb8047d1a939040'),
(92, 'Cellxplosion', 'uploads/92/game.png', 'What if everyone in the world had an explosive telephone in their body? If you could find out their number you can detonate their phone?', 'Top-down action typing game. You must avoid the zombies while destroying them by calling their cell phone numbers.  Survive as long as you can! Link: http://cellxplosion.com/', 'http://cellxplosion.com/', 'http://www.justin.tv/molyjamto/b/313627716', 'Toronto, Canada', 'uploads/92/team.jpg', 'Raymond Tang (Developer), Justin Vanderheide (Developer), Andrew Glisinski (Artist), Jen Costa (Sound Effects), Kyle Johnston (Sound Effects), Ryan Roth (Music)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 232, 48, '2012-04-01 15:24:33', '2012-04-02 09:52:01', 'eb7cc84451fa727d3c938698350ef6a7'),
(93, 'InSanity Sq.', 'uploads/93/game.png', 'Game where your arms are controlled by a psychopath who \r\nkeeps firing guns at innocent people. \r\nYou must turn away from them and run.', 'Try to keep your sanity! But be careful, if people sees you or you become mad, the game is over! Use WASD to move and mouse to aim and fire! If someone stand for too long in our view field you risk to get caught!', 'uploads/93/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1jwnv6csFCg', 'Internet', 'uploads/93/team.jpg', 'InSanity Team is an Italian team composed by:\r\n\r\n// Tato - coding /\r\n\r\n/ Mr. A - art&design /\r\n\r\n/ SbaDany - even MOAR art! /\r\n\r\n/ Midian - design and random stuff that no one else wants to do! //', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 1910, 42, '2012-04-01 15:26:39', '2012-04-03 14:13:01', 'a4213198a2a50423728ff2c5c86dcc7f'),
(94, 'What If Ghosts Could Dream?', 'uploads/94/game.png', 'What if ghosts could dream?', 'a ghost stuck in an apartment learns to dream. a woman that never wakes up. a balcony where no one goes anymore.\r\n\r\nz to interact\r\nx to haunt', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/11720982/GoodnightGhost.swf', '', 'Ottawa, Canada', 'uploads/94/team.jpg', 'sugarbeard', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 8702, 36, '2012-04-01 15:27:45', '2012-04-02 04:54:50', '732c46734f5fb093a6e82d1bcff7688f'),
(95, 'ScareCrow', 'uploads/95/game.jpg', 'You are a scarecrow in a world with just 1 bird', 'Scare the crows to get their diamonds, but if they see you, they try to take them back!\r\n\r\nSee the readme for the full idea (:', 'uploads/95/game.zip', '', 'Dieburg, Germany', '', 'Anneke Eberlei\r\nMarc Kobusch\r\nClaudia Osthof\r\nTobias Kalle\r\nMaik Bärwald', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 135, 23, '2012-04-01 15:28:20', '2012-04-02 12:46:04', '8d52f7052595d67324b0e7f844e15091'),
(96, 'Distortia', 'uploads/96/game.png', 'What if you had the power to distort? What if you had the power to distort reflections?', 'Distortia is a puzzle game that challenges the mind. Using the power of distortion, redirect light beams to target gems.', 'uploads/96/Game_.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Francis Pétrin and Patrick Lalonde', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 189, 31, '2012-04-01 15:28:31', '2012-04-01 19:22:08', '5f448eca613e1a1205871ca44b1dc1c7'),
(97, 'Pigeon Business', 'uploads/97/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'Features include: * Procedurally generated cityscape. * Day and night cycles with changing light. * Suicidal businessmen! * Crazy taxi style gameplay. * Pigeon flying with Wing flaps. * Boost - To give your pigeon that extra speed. * Wing flap streaks. * Skybox.', 'uploads/97/Game_.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lAAFAW3XDMU', 'Montreal, Canada', '', 'Steven Ball (@AlwaysGeeky)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 47153, 54, '2012-04-01 15:29:03', '2012-04-01 20:01:17', 'ce83e6f152e9bd6b770ec7089ad5922f'),
(98, 'Glow, Baby, Glow', 'uploads/98/game.jpg', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'Hey baby, you''re the star of the show! Glow on, little baby, glow on...', 'uploads/98/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/98/team.jpg', 'Duncan Keller', 'CC BY', 'Other', 153, 40, '2012-04-01 15:44:13', '2012-04-01 18:53:26', '4e309599aa83d90db377a710b7a10290'),
(99, 'Rice On The Floor', 'uploads/99/game.jpg', 'Just dropped rice on the floor, am sure there is a game idea here somewhere. http://pic.twitter.com/fu0ZQNTQ', 'PLAY HERE: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/19887116/molyjam_riceonfloor/WebPlayer.html /// \r\n\r\nA competitive hotseat game for 2 players. Players take turns looking for the "short grain" while a timer counts down. WASD to rotate, click + drag to move rice around.\r\n\r\nFor best results, wait a few seconds at the beginning of the game for all the rice to fully generate. \r\n\r\n(Made in 2 hours.)', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/19887116/molyjam_riceonfloor/WebPlayer.html', '', 'NYC, USA', 'uploads/99/team.jpg', 'Wood texture from CGTextures.com /// Robert Yang - everything else.', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 129, 22, '2012-04-01 15:51:17', '2012-04-01 23:22:49', '7f25b9b88b82a2a568416df418833f58'),
(182, 'Ma y Yo Kart', 'uploads/182/game.png', 'Just imagine a kart game where you spend most of the game building one with your mother in a shed, you are the only people alive on earth.', 'Build a kart, survive the apocalypse, and watch mom kick some ass.', 'uploads/182/game.zip', '', 'Seattle, USA', 'uploads/182/team.jpg', 'Ryan Faillace\r\nAndre Stackhouse \r\nGrant Wu\r\nSebastian Bolinger\r\nAaron Cherof\r\n', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 692, 161, '2012-04-01 20:03:40', '2012-04-01 20:51:36', '779498783cbb8e90a8f195da759c8ff1'),
(183, 'The Endless Summer', 'uploads/183/game.jpg', 'You are a scarecrow in a world with just 1 bird', 'You are a scarecrow in a world with just 1 bird.\r\n\r\nThis game dares you to ask the question. It dares you to answer the question. Deux you dare?', 'http://www.newton64.ca/games/jams/molyjam2012/WebPlayer/TheEndlessSummer.html', '', 'Montreal, Canada', 'uploads/183/team.jpg', 'Nick Rudzicz (@newton64)', 'CC BY-SA', 'Unity3D', 171, 25, '2012-04-01 20:10:19', '2012-04-02 05:41:13', 'f2ee30c4b6b8d66f96635ecc792be887'),
(184, 'WAR DOG', 'uploads/184/game.png', 'Modern warfare 3. You play as a dog trying to find his lost family. Music score by Elton John.', 'Find your owner in the aftermath of a battle. Avoid being shot by soldiers. Listen to the smooth sound of Elton John.', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/1156317/war_dog_web/war_dog_web.html', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/184/team.jpg', 'Eddie Cameron (@eddiecameron)', 'CC BY-SA', 'Unity3D', 137, 24, '2012-04-01 20:10:55', '2012-04-01 20:19:04', '5ed28909a4f8e40dcf5f85d767213248'),
(103, 'In Arms'' Way', 'uploads/103/game.png', 'FPS where your arms are controled by a psychopath who keeps firing guns at innocent people. You must turn away from them and run.', '"In Arms'' Way" is a two-player anti-coop game.\r\n<br><br>\r\nControls:<br>\r\nPlayer One:  WASD and arrow keys, or Xbox 360 gamepad<br>\r\nPlayer Two: Mouse to look around, left-click to shoot your pistols and right-click to reload.<br>\r\nR: Restart<br>\r\nM: Return to Main Menu\r\n\r\n<br><br>\r\nDownload from here if download button isn''t working: http://dl.dropbox.com/u/13034099/InArmsWay.zip', 'uploads/103/game.zip', '', 'Montreal, Canada', '', 'Francis Coulombe, Mark Desmarais, Raymond Ortgiesen, Simon Préfontaine', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 142, 4, '2012-04-01 15:52:22', '2012-04-03 08:07:31', 'a1f114fce263e2aec8520f0e61e21c6b'),
(273, 'Path: Romantic Parkour', 'uploads/273/game.jpg', 'Romantic parkour game in which you and the love of your life must hold hands and jump around a city evading death and injury\r\n', 'Two players, three controllers! \r\n\r\nYou’ve lived a long a fruitful life with the one you love. But what would happen if you and your partner had taken a different path? Would your relationship have been as strong? In a metaphorical dreamscape atop city skyscrapers, you find yourself faced with the obstacles that life throws at you. Forever connected on this new adventure following an unfamiliar path.', 'uploads/273/game.zip', 'http://www.twitch.tv/molyjamsf/b/313668265', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/273/team.jpg', 'Mike Kenyon - Programmer\r\nEddie Freeman - Programmer/ Producer\r\nSean Thompson - Level Design/ Play-testing\r\nAnthony Aiello - Environmental Art\r\nCeleste Masinter - Character Design/Modeling and Level Design\r\nJames Snipes - Audio\r\nBrent Jentzsch - Animator', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 12, 5, '2012-04-02 18:06:24', '2012-04-03 09:58:29', '18f43b8d3987d497179fef322cdf7db0'),
(181, 'Ghost Hunt', 'uploads/181/game.png', '"You are a child playing hide&seek, as you hide the world fast forwards. You come out, everyone has died. You must find your friend''s ghosts" "A game where if you touch the floor you die. The only way to progress is to kill enemies and use their body', 'Whilst playing hide and seek with your friends, the world suddenly flashed forward many years, after a devastating event. Now you must find your friends and release their long-dead souls from eternal torment. Watch out for the demons! You can use the ghosts to make paths, at the cost of sending their souls to hell. If you get stuck, return to where you started and click on the tomb stone - it will end the level.', 'uploads/181/game.zip', '', 'Christchurch, New Zealand', '', 'Chris Yee - Art, \r\nGareth Falkingham - Code, \r\nSteven Linton - Code/Sound/Art, \r\nAlister Galpin - Code, \r\nNick Heath - Code, \r\nJohannès Pagwiwoko - Art', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 88, 17, '2012-04-01 19:57:39', '2012-04-01 19:59:19', '773daedb8272eb6e54814bcb16347f07'),
(230, 'Baby GaGa', 'uploads/230/game.jpg', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'You''re trapped in a maze and need to reach one of the level endings to survive. Rock the radioactive baby in your hands at the right pace to make it calm. Naturally, a calm radioactive baby emits more light making navigation easier for you! Avoid all the evil "green" cubes that want to get you and the secret behind the living radioactive baby!', 'uploads/230/game.zip', '', 'Utrecht, Netherlands', 'uploads/230/team.jpg', 'Ruud van Boerdonk\r\nDaniel Harmsen\r\nAram Korevaar\r\nTijn Kersjes \r\nAlex Camilleri\r\nJoeri van Ees\r\nIJke Botman\r\nLaurens de Gier', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 194, 11, '2012-04-02 04:29:36', '2012-04-02 12:54:13', '20881da96ec111cffa5c48e7ee18f6e7'),
