(157, 'flatline', '', '"What if you could plant seeds that grow into cover systems?" (Note: We deviated from this a *lot* More like a ton, really.)', 'Flatline: A game about loss.\r\nSPOILER DESCRIPTION:\r\nImagine a game where you play a game of Pong, but it''s actually a dying father''s heartbeat. The paddles represent holding the father''s hand, holding on for as long as you can. You can walk away, you can give up entirely, but every game ends the same way: at some point,you have to let go.', '', '', 'Internet', '', 'Gabe Deyerle - gdeyerle@gmail.com\r\nWesley Martin - w3martin@gmail.com\r\n\r\nSound effect originally created by User "samfk360" at www.freesoundproject.com', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameMaker', 63, 0, '2012-04-01 18:43:33', '2012-04-01 18:49:09', '0ca7050c22e49bd37c50f3c9b58dd1e8'),
(158, 'Dance Like There''s No Tomorrow', 'uploads/158/game.jpg', 'You regain health by dancing, which you can only do where music is playing. So you need to find musicians or maybe find a rave #danceFPS', 'Stay alive by running to the beat on your dance pad - while jumping over, sliding under and shooting your way through obstacles in a nightclub war zone in an injured solider''s hallucination. Requires 360 DDR pad & 360 Controller to play!', 'uploads/158/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=PkY6eInv73U', 'Internet', '', '@Cat_Musgrove,\r\n@IssamKhalil', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 103, 12, '2012-04-01 18:47:57', '2012-04-02 06:44:08', '49142f2d891ecdde3fca77f4829e2168'),
(160, 'Monster''s Bowl', 'uploads/160/game.jpg', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'A biological weapon that somehow turns people into monsters strikes outside the World Bowling Championships transforming everyone but former world champion Phineas Cronkite.  Phineas constructed bowling balls composed of the monsters'' weaknesses and uses them against his foes.  Additionally combo by spreading splashed weaknesses from one monster to another upon their death.\r\n\r\nhttp://roachpuppy.com/monsters-bowl/', 'http://roachpuppy.com/monsters-bowl/', '', 'Seattle, USA', '', 'Chris Zamanillo (code/art), Aaron Cherof (sound/music)', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 191, 20, '2012-04-01 18:54:38', '2012-04-01 20:42:19', 'c4a4524a27dd2303aacc6caf0009151d'),
(291, 'Plug', 'uploads/291/game.png', 'What if you lived in a world where all guns are required to be plugged into wall sockets? Now THAT would be a tactical shooter wouldn’t it?', 'You are a thief in an appliances shop. You are in trouble and you have to outgun the guards, but your weapon has to be plugged in to be recharged!\r\n\r\nWASD / arrows to move\r\nMouse pointer to aim\r\nLeft click to shoot\r\nHover with the pointer on your plug and attach it to power outlets to recharge', 'uploads/291/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/291/team.jpeg', 'Ciro Continisio - design, programming\r\nPeter Molydeux - concept, inspiration', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 6, 3, '2012-04-03 19:43:09', '2012-04-03 19:43:27', '656ddcfc79583a761f8ee0afbb708235'),
(163, 'Nebulous Hero', 'uploads/163/game.png', 'I''d like to make a game where the tutorial comes up after the credits.', 'What if the tutorial came up after the credits?  Are you even sure what you are really playing?  Play and find out!\r\n\r\nwww.loandbeholdgames.com', 'uploads/163/game.zip', 'http://youtu.be/Ao9tD8xF7qY', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/163/team.png', 'Richard Weschler\r\nShannon Meissner\r\nJon Adamich', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameMaker', 961, 296, '2012-04-01 19:05:55', '2012-04-03 01:59:20', '5ef34fa575282cc7bd77680728e2bb08'),
(164, 'Run Love Run', 'uploads/164/game.png', 'Romantic parkour game in which you and the love of your life must hold hands and jump around a city evading death and injury', 'Run, Love, Run compresses the idea of love into one of synchrony. Jump with your partner, run with your partner, and foster love. Desyncrhonize (run too far ahead, leave the other behind) and the relationship shatters. The world is abstract as the concept, suggesting the airy, surreal experience of love, where you can feel like you''re flying - or falling - or, too often, both.', 'uploads/164/Game_.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Jason Lee\r\nSina Jafarzadeh\r\nJoshua Bell\r\nChelsea Howe\r\nMichael Molinari', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 517, 183, '2012-04-01 19:07:08', '2012-04-01 19:31:16', 'eb590d3e9adbde81d75d802ba73a3293'),
(166, 'Eye of the Babeholder', 'uploads/166/game.jpg', 'Imagine, you play a baby in a pram and can only see your parent''s faces. Studying those faces deeply is the key to true progress.', 'Bababa? Whoosh? Ungh? Whaaa? Burp? Teeheehee?', 'uploads/166/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', '@MutantSparrow @RadioSachka', 'CC BY', 'Other', 106, 19, '2012-04-01 19:10:01', '2012-04-02 16:22:28', '1dcdc9b016b16b06dd8e4f2e9b75178c'),
(167, 'Number Seventeen Cherry Tree Lane', 'uploads/167/game.png', 'Hey @americanmcgee, we should work together and make a Mary Poppins game. I have loads of ideas involving umbrella mechanics.', 'American Mcgee''s Mary Poppins is not your typical British Nanny. Saving / kidnapping  supposed abused children, Mary uses here Umbrella to navigate through the rooftops of Cherry Tree Lane and in some cases, grapple misbehaving children.', 'uploads/167/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/167/team.jpg', 'Bill Kiley\r\nGeorge Katsaros,\r\nJohn Park\r\nArif Qazi,\r\nJeffrey Fernandez\r\n', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 160, 19, '2012-04-01 19:10:03', '2012-04-02 23:56:35', 'd9d08992181599787071480511500ada'),
(186, 'Radioactive Multiplayer Baby Rocker Racing', 'uploads/186/game.png', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'Race against your friends to see who can save their poor radioactive baby from certain doom.  Don''t rock the baby too much for fear of deadly radiation.', 'http://rmbrr.ianguthridge.com', 'http://www.twitch.tv/molyjamsf/b/313733576', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/186/team.jpeg', 'Kelsey Martin - Art\r\nIan Guthridge - Dev/Design\r\nTrevor Adams - Dev\r\nDaniel Plemmons - Design/Dev\r\nBill Kiley - Audio\r\n\r\nNote:  All team members made significant contributions in all fields of the game.  Listed roles just note their primary focus.', 'CC BY-ND', 'Other', 1076, 195, '2012-04-01 20:27:02', '2012-04-02 18:22:14', 'cba36726a36ba9c0ce00c3e6343bc1cc'),
(171, 'Blowback', '', 'You are a small girl flying a talking kite. The kite seems to know about a upcoming major terrorist attack and floats towards clues.', '"Blowback" - By JForce (@JForceGames)', 'uploads/171/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/171/team.jpg', 'Game by Jeremy Eden, Jonny Eden & Ty Dauster -- http://jforcegames.com -- \r\n\r\nMusic by Kevin MacLeod -- http://incompetech.com', 'CC BY', 'XNA', 64986, 156, '2012-04-01 19:22:21', '2012-04-01 21:36:31', '8251083f1b27f03fa07dd969491e93bd'),
(172, 'pigeon', 'uploads/172/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'Game: \r\nPrevent depressed businessmen from leaping to their death by fetching items that remind them of love from their homes. As a pigeon. [GAME: http://hazzens.com/pigeon/pigeon.html ||\r\nSOURCE: https://github.com/hazzen/pigeon]', 'http://hazzens.com/pigeon/pigeon.html', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Mikey (@hazzen)', 'CC BY-SA', 'None', 190, 39, '2012-04-01 19:22:57', '2012-04-01 19:24:19', '7d1bfa159da85fcb10610b6b312d86b5'),
(197, 'Black and Rice 2: Battle of the Gods', 'uploads/197/game.jpg', 'Just dropped rice on the floor, am sure there is a game idea here somewhere. http://pic.twitter.com/fu0ZQNTQ', 'Rice was dropped, the world was changed. You must drop your rice ball from the heavens to appease the Twitter Gods, but keep the resulting grains (50 per level) from dropping into the abyss below.', 'http://cagames.com/blackandrice2/bnr2.html', '', 'Austin, USA', 'uploads/197/team.jpg', 'Nick Fofi\r\nRoddy Toomim', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 262, 52, '2012-04-01 21:30:46', '2012-04-01 21:30:47', 'dcbfa8b7f7bba501599203b6650a5b74'),
(176, 'A Roll of Silence', 'uploads/176/game.png', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'Players must survive against "horrible" "monsters" using the fantastic power of the bowling arm!', 'uploads/176/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/176/team.png', 'Ryan Schaefer - Art/Programming/Design\r\n@Digitalistic\r\nRyanLSchaefer@gmail.com', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 91, 13, '2012-04-01 19:26:09', '2012-04-01 23:15:00', '7695e8ba2992877dca9fb55fa0557935'),
(177, 'COO', 'uploads/177/game.png', 'You are a pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade businessmen not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their homes.', 'A glimpse into the darkness that lies within the soul of every man and pigeon.', 'uploads/177/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=CoAUHgIDkBc', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/177/team.jpg', 'Brandon Dillon,\r\nJolie Menzel,\r\nJonathon Banks,\r\nKevin Gadd,\r\nJP LeBreton', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 2002, 562, '2012-04-01 19:29:51', '2012-04-02 19:55:03', 'fcec2291d40b7defb83bf39b9cb38511'),
(178, 'Meant Only For the Righteous', 'uploads/178/game.png', '"We''ve had emotional game endings but have we ever had an emotional title screen?"\r\n...\r\n"I''m currently exploring the idea of making a game that begins with a gameover screen where you can''t continue."', 'A videogame about self-righteous judgment, for self-righteous judgers.', 'http://www.godatplay.com/MeantOnlyForTheRighteous/', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/178/team.jpg', 'Josh Larson', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 90, 18, '2012-04-01 19:30:08', '2012-04-01 19:32:56', '74b84a58eb8706860e2d9f784cfc4711'),
(179, 'Hugman', 'uploads/179/game.jpg', 'Imagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other. You on the other hand, your only ability is to hug those around you.', 'Hugman is a single screen 2D game. The titular character is a mute,  who has invited his family to a party.\r\n\r\nIt doesn''t take long for all the feuds to erupt in to chaos. \r\nUsing the only social interaction he knows, Hugman must try to calm his irate relatives and prevent an all out war.', 'uploads/179/game.zip', '', 'Dundee, UK', 'uploads/179/team.jpg', '3 Students from the University of Abertay, Dundee:\r\nBryn Morrisson-Elliott (Artist, Audio), \r\nEmily Green (Artist), \r\nJohn Cooper (Programmer)', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 1307, 468, '2012-04-01 19:31:43', '2012-04-02 13:18:30', 'dac1cd95ec51b1e74bd75926abbc9af9'),
(203, 'OSO2', 'uploads/203/game.png', 'You are a bear but for some reason your oxygen comes from hugging people. Problem is that hugging people breaks their bones. #Poeticgaming\r\n\r\nImagine living in a world where all anyone can do is hurt each other. You on the other hand, your only abili', 'A bear''s dying wishes to go into space and hug as much as possible.\r\n\r\nBoth Mac OS X and Windows versions are on our game''s website: http://everythingafter.net/OSO2/', 'uploads/203/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/203/team.jpg', 'Chuck Jordan, Andrew Langley, Tulley Rafferty, John "Seg" Seggerson, Music by: Amanda Rose Smith', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 281, 46, '2012-04-01 21:51:34', '2012-04-02 10:43:46', 'ae9dbe01d50165bed2e941fe6c2ddc19'),
(248, 'Labyrinthian', 'uploads/248/game.png', '(...) what if killing enemies makes them fall to the floor and point towards the exit? That''s the only way to find your way out.', 'LABYRINTHIAN is a glorious-trainwreck-type game thing that I put together in the idle time between organizing the Montréal Molyjam.\r\nI did not originally plan to make a game at all, so this was rushed into "completion" on the last day.', 'uploads/248/game.zip', '', 'Montreal, Canada', 'uploads/248/team.png', 'The blue horses were drawn by Francis Coulombe aka FrankieSmileShow, pixel artist extraordinaire!\r\nThe background is a picture from a CD-ROM of the Yangshuo County, a crop of which was used for the Phobos background of Doom''s first episode.\r\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yangshuo_County\r\nThe music is a MIDI rendering of Aladdin''s "A Whole New World", no copyright infrigment intended of course.\r\nI (Renaud Bédard) did the rest!', 'CC BY', 'XNA', 126, 20, '2012-04-02 10:44:43', '2012-04-02 10:44:44', 'e3dcc90e30a3a7c7cbf526d7c82a5bd5'),
(204, 'Tree-Light', 'uploads/204/game.jpg', 'What if you were half man half tree? You can only fight when in soil and constantly grow throughout the game.', 'You control a half-tree girl that must use the energy of the world to bring her "underworld" back to life.', 'uploads/204/game.zip', '', 'Guadalajara, Mexico', '', 'Rubén Medellín, Pablo Arias Pérez, NikanoruS', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 84, 16, '2012-04-01 22:01:59', '2012-04-03 10:11:53', 'ec424c2fd809a90be3f9758a1bfaef58'),
(205, 'Big-Business Morale Pigeon', 'uploads/205/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'You are a big city pigeon just trying to scape by with $1 trillion.', 'http://pixieengine.com/projects/1727/fullscreen', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TMmOMgrCT5M&list=UUARi9HUgGrTdULOwIsytarg&index=1&feature=plcp', 'Oakland / East Bay, USA', '', 'Matt Diebolt - Programming, art.\r\nDaniel X. Moore - Backgrounds, Title Screen, music.\r\nLoren Schmit - Photoshop Background consultant.', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 88, 13, '2012-04-01 22:03:36', '2012-04-01 22:28:46', '681501d1a777606f95f96fee4eea4ae3'),
(206, 'The Green Pixel', '', 'Service has resumed and the first jam is about to kick off but believe me that is not the last you''ll see of that pesky green pixel', 'Just a day in the life of a green pixel...  Nah, it''s a bit more awesome than that!  Travel through space!  Be eaten by a snake!  Put on a beautiful firework display!  All this and more!\r\n<br>\r\nFollow the progress of the game at:\r\n<br>\r\n\r\n<a href = "http://www.kerryallen.com/tag/the-green-pixel/">http://www.kerryallen.com/tag/the-green-pixel/</a>', 'uploads/206/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wDKlOc5lpro', 'Orlando, USA', 'uploads/206/team.jpg', 'Kerry Allen (Programmer, Designer, Artist)\r\nJohn Ryan (Audio)', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'XNA', 99, 2, '2012-04-01 22:04:38', '2012-04-02 20:57:40', '6456d76714680c45314bc3b031895b27'),
(207, 'Uninvited', '', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors? Could add more depth by having dirty mirrors that need to be cleaned?\r\n\r\nAND\r\n\r\nTry to imagine a game in which you have an imaginary friend who doesn’t believe you are real, you must ', 'Flash adventure game featuring hand-drawn graphics and a chilling story! Well... that''s if we had time to finish the game. ', 'uploads/207/game.zip', '', 'Internet', '', 'Benjamin Crocker\r\nTony Gaskell\r\nTony Loiseleur\r\nVince Loiseleur\r\nJose Marzan\r\nKalvin Tran', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 98, 28, '2012-04-01 22:11:01', '2012-04-01 22:11:02', '18cb078c3cc801073e55e326257bdf01'),
(234, 'Holding the baby', 'uploads/234/game.jpg', 'You play a babysitter, you turn up and the baby is made of cardboard. Would you stay? I want games to start asking more ethical questions.', 'A physical game that is by turns creepy, awkward and hilarious.\r\n\r\nhttp://v21.posterous.com/holding-the-baby', 'http://v21.posterous.com/holding-the-baby', '', 'London, UK', '', 'George Buckenham (@v21)\r\nAlan Hazelden (@draknek)', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 142, 20, '2012-04-02 06:02:22', '2012-04-02 06:02:24', '07a37f6872b3f1e53f7e354a7205580c'),
(208, 'What if you could CLIMB text', 'uploads/208/game.png', 'What if everyone in the game had text constantly around them expressing their feelings? Now, imagine in this game you can CLIMB text?', 'Grapple onto words and collect words with the goal letter before the time runs out! But watch out, the words disappear when you hop off of them.\r\n\r\nControls:\r\nLeft/Right arrows keys move left and right. Space key to jump, and press the up key while jumping to climb onto a letter.', 'uploads/208/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Andrew G. Crowell - (programming, art - @Bananattack), Luke Rewega (programming, art - @lrewega), Bill Kiley (music - bill.kiley@gmail.com)', 'CC BY-SA', 'None', 205, 34, '2012-04-01 22:16:38', '2012-04-02 23:29:25', '39bb4d99d6038623e697c2a37956ee2f'),
(209, 'QWE (Qarrots, Wadishes n'' ''Ettuce)', 'uploads/209/game.png', 'You control a mystical rabbit at a bus stop during Winter. You must find as many creative ways as possible to make people miss their buses.', 'Eat veggies and use their power to cast emotion-manipulating spells on people at bus stops until they have emotional breakdowns and run off screaming.', 'uploads/209/game.zip', '', 'Oakland / East Bay, USA', 'uploads/209/team.jpg', '@NoGasta (Scott LaGrasta)', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 169, 26, '2012-04-01 22:18:20', '2012-04-02 23:14:51', '24519714adc666e017b59942ea80c2a6'),
(210, 'Let''s Protest!', 'uploads/210/game.png', 'Imagine a game in which you have to join protests to make changes to the rules within the game''s world.', 'The world is constructed against you (duh), but at least you can protest. Tired of the weather? Protest for a change! Sick of poor movement? Protest!\r\n\r\nGo play: http://www.kongregate.com/games/IcarusTyler/lets-protest', 'uploads/210/game.zip', '', 'Internet', 'uploads/210/team.png', 'Matthias Zarzecki, www.matthewongamedesign.com, @IcarusTyler', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 919, 226, '2012-04-01 22:19:43', '2012-04-04 02:41:13', '8f40531b31c616f21adc1ff61cb705d0'),
(211, 'NukaBaby', 'uploads/211/game.jpg', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc /\r\nA survival horror game where you have to sing lullabies to your 2 year old to stop them from screaming/cry', 'NukaBaby is a 2 player competitive game inspired by two tweets. One player is the Hero, who must collect stars to feed his radioactive baby; the second player is the Overlord, who summons monsters to ambush him.  The baby naturally glows, but can be soothed by the Hero''s singing.  However, eye monsters are attracted to light, while ear monsters are attracted to sound.  The player can lure the monsters into traps or trick them into eating each other.\r\nWindows and OSX executables are included.', 'uploads/211/game.zip', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Brendon Chung, Daniel Herrera, Wallace Huang, & James Liu', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 658, 53, '2012-04-01 22:31:00', '2012-04-01 22:36:37', '5bc3fc2921181bb3d4749b8bcedcc1a8'),
