(221, 'Six', 'uploads/221/game.png', '"You know in cut scenes when it says ''3 months later...''? What if the game ACTUALLY locked your save file for 3 months?" and "What if games rewarded you for believing rather than winning?"', 'Six scenes, played over six consecutive days.\r\n\r\nMade using Flixel.', 'http://reallyfancy.com/games/six/', '', 'Brighton, UK', 'uploads/221/team.jpg', 'Kerry Turner', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 347, 60, '2012-04-02 00:29:07', '2012-04-02 00:34:33', 'cc396b09d02b62da92c31e9bf4821657'),
(222, 'Revenge Of The Road', 'uploads/222/game.jpg', 'Have you ever played a racing game and wanted to play as the road rather than the cars? I know I have...', 'Revenge of the Road\r\n\r\nPlayer 1 - The Ship\r\nControl the ship with A and D to stay on the road.\r\nStay on the road for 30 seconds to win.\r\n\r\nPlayer 2 - The Road\r\nControl the path of the road with the arrow keys, up, down, left and right. \r\nShake off the player to win!\r\n', 'http://www.dannygoodayle.com/2012/04/01/molyjam-2012-revenge-of-the-road/', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lL--MwvUdUA&feature=youtu.be', 'London, UK', '', 'Danny Goodayle \r\nJames Simm\r\nChapman Lee\r\nWilliam Robinson\r\nMaksims Mihejevs\r\nChris Bean\r\nRobyn Nevison\r\nRoberta Saliani\r\nThomas Clarke\r\nPaul Sinnett', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 440, 71, '2012-04-02 00:45:59', '2012-04-02 14:24:14', '19635f041528c0c8a2eaf78da87cdd1d'),
(223, 'OCTOPI EVERYTHING', 'uploads/223/game.png', 'Online sidescrolling co-op 8 player game where each person controls a leg of a octopus. Each leg can attach guns which the player can fire', '8 players collectively control on Octopus trying to go as deep as possible.\r\n\r\nYou can play 8 players on a single keyboard or if you have node.js each player can control their limb with their iPhone or Android phone.', 'http://greggman.github.com/octopus/octopus.html', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Kirk George @FoozleMoozle,\r\nGregg Tavares @greggman,\r\nShelley Monahan @shellethkin,\r\nStephanie Tang @flavortang', 'CC BY', 'None', 437, 71, '2012-04-02 00:46:04', '2012-04-02 13:06:44', '0aaeac2757e74ebdb3cebffc71663aa7'),
(224, 'I, Crow-Bot™', 'uploads/224/game.jpg', 'You are a scarecrow in a world with just 1 bird', 'You Control a robot scarecrow in a world with only one crow left. Can you save the corn without violating the three laws of Crow-Botics?', 'http://i.crow-bot.com/', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Harrison Pink, Eric Parsons, Doug Tabacco, and Charlie Huguenard. Music by Chris Remo.', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Unity3D', 293, 49, '2012-04-02 00:50:18', '2012-04-02 00:51:12', '81c5f5d49d2178dd6309c02d28c77227'),
(225, 'Tethyrd', 'uploads/225/game.png', 'What if you lived in a world where all guns are required to be plugged into wall sockets? Now THAT would be a tactical shooter wouldn''t it?', 'Tethyrd (pronounced "tethered") is a top-down shmuplike that requires the player to be tethered to a power outlet to shoot projectiles. The trick is guiding the plug into the socket while avoiding the enemy onslaught.\r\n--\r\nPlay: http://www.kodewerx.org/tethyrd.swf\r\n--\r\nControls: WASD to move, mouse cursor to aim, mouse button to shoot (when plugged in), E to unplug.', 'http://www.kodewerx.org/tethyrd.swf', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/225/team.jpg', 'Seth Robles (Art) -\r\nBill Kiley (Music, sound effects) -\r\nDavid Townsend (Design, programming) -\r\nJay Oster (Programming, design) -\r\nRomy Ilano (Level design, support) -\r\nOlly Quinn (Support, ideas)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 299, 75, '2012-04-02 01:36:42', '2012-04-02 12:12:17', 'eeab9dc8c269c810d6f0fa428cb7157d'),
(226, 'Recidivism', 'uploads/226/game.png', 'Imagine if when you kill someone their death animation loops and ''burns'' into your screen so you have to watch it for the rest of the game?', 'An HTML5 game where you play a compulsive killer who is forced to relive the deaths of everyone he has murdered in his past.', 'http://johndriscoll.name/recidivism/', 'http://youtu.be/RkSh6BfswIg', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'John Driscoll(@johndriskull), Jonathan Ghazarian(@SomeGuyJG), Jeffrey Schwinghammer(@JSchwinghammer), Mauricio Balvanera, Damian Sol', 'CC BY-NC', 'None', 1690, 452, '2012-04-02 01:55:38', '2012-04-03 10:34:31', 'a5471d5a97eddb7bbab7ea314ce57baa'),
(227, 'In the dark, the blind can see', 'uploads/227/game.png', 'A survival horror game where you have to sing lullabies to your 2 year old to stop them from screaming/crying and giving your position away', 'Can a blind man still protect his son from the soldiers that invade his home?', 'uploads/227/game.zip', '', 'Dieburg, Germany', '', 'Oliver Eberlei - Programming / Game Design\r\nMohaned Shilaih - Level Design\r\n\r\nAdditional Help:\r\nTobias Kalle - Puzzle Design\r\nMatthias Laren - Main Character Animation', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Unity3D', 138, 25, '2012-04-02 02:46:10', '2012-04-02 02:46:11', 'ce7d136609870102eb294cd2e444d228'),
(228, 'GhostDad 2 Colon Cats Vs. Merlins', 'uploads/228/game.jpg', 'I cheated: I didn''t get inspired by Peter Molydeux. I used to work with that dude, and I''m pretty sure he''s just tweeting my diary.\r\n\r\nSo I went to the source.\r\n\r\nMe. ', 'An exploration of the Jungian model of psychic introspection and projection of insecurities onto Merlins who chase you around the room.\r\n\r\nYou are a Ghost Dad of 3 daughters who have three cats who you must use to scare the collective unconscious of your soul away.\r\n\r\nIt uses your voice to attract and repel your fears, fantasies, delusions and cats.', 'uploads/228/game.zip', '', 'London, UK', '', 'Aubrey Hesselgren,\r\nChris Cox', 'CC BY-SA', 'Unity3D', 443, 105, '2012-04-02 02:57:33', '2012-04-02 02:59:04', 'a7dbb74c98b08d7a3d47a4ba1ef9f03f'),
(229, 'PH S CT X: The invisible FPS', 'uploads/229/game.jpg', 'Would love to make a corridor shooter but where all walls are invisible. Constantly worrying if that enemy has open space to aim at you.\r\n\r\nTweet link: http://t.co/rQHCnEzr', 'First person shooter where most everything is invisible. The walls, your gun and shots, the powerups, and even some of the enemies. ', 'uploads/229/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Game: Hanford Lemoore \r\nMusic: Bill Kiley \r\nContact: http://twitter.com/hanfordlemoore \r\nhttp://hanfordlemoore.com ', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 277, 88, '2012-04-02 03:04:50', '2012-04-02 03:53:09', 'e877e818c972bd850587452f175e7ea0'),
(231, 'Little Miss Left Behind', 'uploads/231/game.jpg', 'Game where you must hold onto your mother’s hand. Let go for more than X seconds and it’s game over.', 'What if you actually had to reach up and hold your mothers hand? Using kinect and the awesome power of pure physical emotional feedback, Little Miss Left Behind throws you into the shoes of Molly, a girl whose path is littered with temptation, danger, and a dynamic soundtrack which will get stuck in your head.<br /><br />\r\n\r\nRequires Kinect to play. Please follow installation instructions in README.txt for more info.', 'uploads/231/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1hawgT6d6sk', 'London, UK', '', 'Code: Wolfgang Graebner https://twitter.com/#!/FunstormGames<br />\r\n\r\nArt: Sarah Ford https://twitter.com/#!/AngelosLH<br />\r\n\r\nAudio: Shaz Yousaf https://twitter.com/#!/HoneyTribeStu<br />\r\n\r\nInspiration: Peter Molydeux', 'CC BY', 'None', 275, 15, '2012-04-02 04:32:02', '2012-04-02 04:36:01', 'df143e6dd8e095d191f23adfe565a0bf'),
(232, 'Comedecoy', 'uploads/232/game.jpg', 'Imagine being able to verbally tell a funny joke to a guard and causing him to roll over laughing allowing you past?', 'You''re a comedian decoy. Tell the right joke to make the guard laugh so your heist partner can sneak past.\r\n\r\nHave a conversation to figure out each guard''s sense of humour but pay attention to the emotions on their face. Bore them or make them angry and they''ll start looking over your shoulder.\r\n\r\nUse keyboard numbers to pick dialogue or J to tell a joke.', 'uploads/232/game.zip', '', 'London, UK', '', 'Programmer/Designer - Tom Smith @TomSmizzle, \r\nArtist - Ross Cubbon @RossCubbon,\r\nArtist - David French @TheDonquixotic, Artist - Fraser Ntukula @fraserntukula,\r\nWriter/Designer - Debbie Timmins @Weefz', 'CC BY', 'GameMaker', 380, 70, '2012-04-02 04:41:32', '2012-04-02 04:43:53', 'e758de712ac921a36713eff90ca7292c'),
(233, 'I''m Blind!', 'uploads/233/game.jpg', 'I also love the idea of playing a character who is PRETENDING to be blind, so you have to keep bumping into things to not arouse suspicion.', 'I''m Blind is a multiplayer game where you and other players have gate crashed a party for the rich and the blind. In order to maximum your serving size at the dinner, you must accuse others of not being blind in order for them to be kicked out of the party.', 'http://www.digitalconfectioners.com/content/im-blind', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=St4a5qpbFpg', 'Christchurch, New Zealand', '', 'James Tan - Jack of all trades\r\nSam Evans - Testing\r\nAlex Gray - Testing\r\nRyan McKee - Testing\r\nMike Adair - Testing\r\nAlastair Cameron - Music (Free Music Archive)', 'CC BY', 'Unreal', 174, 39, '2012-04-02 04:56:54', '2012-04-02 04:56:57', '29b8521e042af06441f745c81898bdcc'),
(235, 'You Are The Road', 'uploads/235/game.jpg', 'Have you ever played a racing game and wanted to play as the road rather than the cars? I know I have...', 'You control the road. Your movements affect the cars and their emotions. What do you do?\r\n<br /><br />\r\n(this is a web game - choosing "download" will play the game in your browser)', 'http://robotduck.com/YouAreTheRoad/', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oEQsJzjUm30', 'Internet', 'uploads/235/team.jpg', 'Ben Pitt (@robotduck)', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 1009, 241, '2012-04-02 06:32:52', '2012-04-03 05:35:24', 'bd429e2b2ceabf91c59585264af3511b'),
(238, 'Museum of You', 'uploads/238/game.png', 'How about something completely new? A game where you have to pay tribute to someone, collect everything about them and create a museum?', 'If I had more time, there would be more types of underwear.\r\n\r\nhttp://nottheinternet.com/games/museumofyou/', 'http://nottheinternet.com/games/museumofyou/', '', 'London, UK', '', 'George Buckenham (@v21)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 141, 13, '2012-04-02 06:45:20', '2012-04-02 06:46:03', '34355e716844f150ae3d3b03724c9c60'),
(237, 'sick peter', 'uploads/237/game.png', 'I want to make a World War 2 game. What? been done before? No, you see in MY game you don''t control a solider but a 4 year old child.', 'Peter is a 4 year old Jewish boy who has lost his mother in Nazi-occupied Holland.  He is also terminally ill.  Help him avoid the guards and find his lost Moma, but be wary of his gradually weakening condition.\r\n\r\n(Made in 5 hours on April 1st at the London Molyjam.  Check readme file for instructions.)', 'uploads/237/game.zip', '', 'London, UK', 'uploads/237/team.jpg', 'Darren Grey (@darrenjohngrey)', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 282, 45, '2012-04-02 06:42:39', '2012-04-02 17:21:47', 'e8b67dcfa166db764a3d3450d446b850'),
(266, 'Emille', 'uploads/266/game.png', '-FPS War game, you control the teddy bear of a child who has just escaped a death camp. Help them find their mother using your wits.\r\n<br>-Game where you must hold onto your mother''s hand. Let go for more than X seconds and it''s game over', 'Emille is a 2D side-scroller made for tablet devices. It will be released for iOS and Android! The main character, Emille, only has her Teddy Bear. Each level challenges you to either throw the teddy bear or drop the teddy bear on a switch to get to the door. Be careful though, you start to fade away every second you go without your teddy bear. Race the clock to beat each level, leading Emille back home!\r\n<br>Website: http://emillegame.com/\r\n<br>Soundtrack: http://bit.ly/Hgekfo', 'uploads/266/game.zip', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Kenan Alpay - Level Designer\r\n<br>Christine Farmer - Conceptual Artist\r\n<br>Juan Gallardo - Producer/Web Manager\r\n<br>Scott Hernandez - Art Director\r\n<br>Matthew Herz - Lead Programmer\r\n<br>Corey Lay - Lead Designer\r\n<br>Ernest Maynard - Animator\r\n<br>Steven Oliveira - Game Designer\r\n<br>Sean Ursani - Composer ', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameSalad', 17, 2, '2012-04-02 16:13:08', '2012-04-04 15:26:18', '24ae9511c5736e91bc45705c14a66126'),
(239, 'You Cheating Pirate!', 'uploads/239/game.jpg', 'Can you imagine, just imagine a game where the enemies are actually able to use cheat codes? ', 'http://www.samuelbarker.co.uk/images/YouCheatingPirateName.swf \r\n\r\nYarrr, save the traders from those scurvy-ridden pirates!\r\nBut beware the bilge-suckin'' cheat codes or ye''ll soon be walkin'' the plank!', 'http://www.samuelbarker.co.uk/images/YouCheatingPirateName.swf', '', 'London, UK', '', 'Samuel Barker', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 105, 18, '2012-04-02 07:44:24', '2012-04-02 07:44:25', '813bce2373f7fc71ef70d9a6a4b49c73'),
(240, 'Babies (and possibly Snakes) On A Plane', 'uploads/240/game.png', 'Game in which you must comfort children on a plane who are afraid of flying, game mechanic is similar to spinning plates.', 'A puzzle game where you Samuel and your partner Samuel have to keep the babies on the plane from freaking out and shitting themselves. Work together or get in each others way. The game gets harder every minute.', 'uploads/240/game.zip', '', 'Brighton, UK', '', 'Andy Kaminski - Programming\r\nRyan Timpany - Graphics', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'None', 93, 16, '2012-04-02 07:51:59', '2012-04-02 09:34:06', '191a821b5d2b4c061e0f2fd87ffa3339'),
(241, 'Dead Balls', 'uploads/241/game.png', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'Survive against the deadly pins!\r\n\r\nhttp://www.robotpandaproductions.com/manticore/manticore.html', 'http://www.robotpandaproductions.com/manticore/manticore.html', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/241/team.jpg', 'Lee Petty\r\nDrew Skillman\r\nAlex Vaughan\r\nBill Gahr\r\nPatrick Connor', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 698, 57, '2012-04-02 08:28:27', '2012-04-02 09:03:26', '6d271070e1fc117bb0075520cf51d951'),
(242, 'Phone Frag!', 'uploads/242/game.png', 'What if everyone in the world had an explosive telephone in their body? If you could find out their number you can detonate their phone?', 'the Men in Block are after your beloved dog! Are they aliens? are they gov''t cronies? all you know is that they have telephones inside their bodies, and if you dial the right number from an old school phone booth, you can get rid of them! Take your trusty Dog around town and lead her to trashcans, dumpsters, and other green glowy objects and see what she digs up -it could be power ups or phone numbers! if the enemy makes it to your house, your Dog takes damage! too much, and its Game Over!', 'uploads/242/game.zip', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Man Vs.Games:\r\nJason Neal\r\nAaron Habibipour', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Unity3D', 97, 23, '2012-04-02 09:09:54', '2012-04-02 09:12:22', '25ddc29a60d1551e65d9794dd4e10e72'),
(243, 'Far From the Tree', 'uploads/243/game.png', 'What if you could plant seeds that grow into cover systems? \r\n\r\nWhat if a cover system had raw emotion? i.e having to use dead people that you loved as a means of cover?', 'A solitary apple tree grows in a high tower, in a fortress in a barren land. Its apples long to escape the fortress and repopulate the land outside, but the fortress is filled with deadly hazards and patrolled by sinister eyeballs. The odds are insurmountable for a single apple, but each apple''s sacrifice is not in vain; the corpses of apples who didn''t make it remain rooted in the fortress where they fell, creating cover to hide from the eyeballs, and even bridges to traverse pits of lava.', 'uploads/243/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ig5lMu2t3E0', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'R. Hunter Gough', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 102, 19, '2012-04-02 09:41:05', '2012-04-02 11:56:39', '95646010d9f008e5de8fd876d59df4fd'),
(244, 'ZOMBIE STRIKE', '', '"Genre : Action, Survival Horror Survival Horror combined with Bowling "', 'Mass hordes of zombies with your lucky bowling ball and a pin luancher. Can you survive\r\n\r\n', '', '', 'Orlando, USA', '', 'Patrick Rasmussen \r\nw/ special thinks to those who explained things that I did not know yet,,', 'CC BY-SA', 'GameMaker', 81, 0, '2012-04-02 09:54:16', '2012-04-02 09:54:17', '342738db8cac6fa66f365c0a36fcffcf'),
(245, 'Escape from Alcatraz', 'uploads/245/game.png', 'What if you lived in a world where all guns are required to be plugged into wall sockets? Now THAT would be a tactical shooter wouldn’t it?', 'Tug of war. Reach the other team''s camp while defending yours.', 'http://uken.github.com/chords', '', 'Toronto, Canada', 'uploads/245/team.jpg', 'Jeremy Williams\r\nHamsharan Mahalingam\r\nJen Costa\r\nPitr Vernigorov', 'CC BY', 'None', 90, 17, '2012-04-02 10:06:15', '2012-04-02 10:06:17', '41c6654bb2c9b1a894b11ea685fd3c7b'),
(246, 'Friends ''til the end', 'uploads/246/game.png', 'You play as a small boy with a remote control helicoptor that is alive and your friend, then you discover a nuclear missle inside it', 'You play as Bobby, a little kid with a remote controlled helicopter named Choppy. His bestest friend! However, he finds out he''s equipped with a nuclear missile. Help Choppy reach a scientist that will disarm him from this world ending handicap. Watch out for those battery levels on your way to eternal friendship.', 'uploads/246/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W3UCpBfVLT0', 'Montreal, Canada', '', 'Jean Chan\r\nJustin Cyr\r\nJonathan Lavigne\r\nJean-Francois Major\r\nFrancis Coulombe\r\nRenaud "Monster King"', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'XNA', 1020, 159, '2012-04-02 10:07:03', '2012-04-02 10:33:02', '78d7cf34f561963a1d69ebc0dc761526'),
(247, '28 Frames Later: Gutters of Blood', 'uploads/247/game.png', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'A simple arcade-style bowling game... only with scarce ammunition (balls!), lots of fog, and zombies!', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/10126483/GuttersOfBlood/WebPlayer/webplayer.html', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Peter Hunter,\r\nBill Kiley,\r\nBen Mears,\r\nDan Miller-Schroeder,\r\nCasey Noland,\r\nChris Osborn,\r\nJohn Peters,\r\nMax Weinberg', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 184, 40, '2012-04-02 10:42:52', '2012-04-02 12:10:38', '9179eb3df4d56f89959e4f9e19c2b39f'),
(249, 'Amour Parkour', 'uploads/249/game.jpg', 'Romantic parkour game in which you and the love of your life must hold hands and jump around a city evading death and injury', 'A 2-player coop action game where communication and cooperation are as important as your own skills.', 'http://saygt.com/amourparkour', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Ryan Cousins(environments),\r\nBeverly Sage(animation),\r\nSeiji Tanaka(programming)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 190, 36, '2012-04-02 10:53:30', '2012-04-02 19:13:58', 'ead851fd9375cdad0d24a1d5252b3aed'),
(250, 'Goat has a trasformative experience traveling in space', 'uploads/250/game.png', 'Make a film about a horse, you get awards. Make a game about a horse, you get laughed at', 'This is a game that has a goat who decides to travel in space but learns a lot about himself and the transformative nature of planetary travel while selling bones. There are two secrets. The whole game is html/javascript and I only tested in Chrome.\r\n\r\nArrow keys to move, mouse to buy things.', 'http://bennorskov.com/GAAAAAME/index.html', '', 'NYC, USA', 'uploads/250/team.jpg', 'Ben N.', 'CC BY', 'Other', 118, 18, '2012-04-02 11:20:17', '2012-04-02 11:40:07', 'db0d225b2b284b0b0fd637c86eece624'),
(251, 'Attached to Verticals', 'uploads/251/game.png', 'Can you visualise a world where horizontal is impossible? You are forever falling or attached to verticals?\r\n+\r\nAn action game where your character is constantly falling. You can hang onto things but only for 1-3 seconds', 'Visit http://attachedtoverticals.com or open the index page in the zip file with your browser. Works best in Chrome.\r\n\r\n> Arrow keys to move left and right\r\n> Avoid verticals in the face\r\n> Attach to verticals to slow down\r\n> Super skillz will engage Moly*eux mode (or hit ''m'')\r\n> Excuse the bugs\r\n', 'uploads/251/game.zip', '', 'Brighton, UK', '', '> Source codes: Eddy Parris\r\n> Sound waves: Joe Chung\r\n> Awesome sauces: Jo Summers', 'CC BY', 'Other', 72, 18, '2012-04-02 11:30:19', '2012-04-03 09:04:27', '1dc6c10a2e525e3feab134e5fbdf0f4a'),
(252, 'Bunny Bus-ter', 'uploads/252/game.png', 'You control a mystical rabbit at a bus stop during Winter. You must find as many creative ways as possible to make people miss their buses.', 'Use your mystical burrowing power to prevent buses from reaching their bus stops and disrupting traffic. But watch out, traffic can kill you too! <br/><br>\r\n\r\nOur team comprised one developer and three artists. We wanted to make a game that would also convert well for a touch screen device if we decide to make the change later.', 'http://davefeldman.com/bunny', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uQtLcVSwJ20', 'Las Vegas, USA', '', 'Sheila Antonio\r\nDave Feldman\r\nVincent Leyba\r\nBo Lockwood', 'CC BY', 'None', 83, 16, '2012-04-02 11:31:58', '2012-04-02 12:53:23', '7c0e1a4844b993093b5480ce893f970d'),
(259, 'Shake, Rattle, and Glow', 'uploads/259/game.jpg', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'Flash game made for MolyJam 2012, a 48 hour game jam hosted by Magic Pixel games in Culver city. Programming by Eric Medine and Jessica Kim, art by Joshua Harris and Cat Sze.\r\n\r\nYou have to progress thru the level, using radiation to open doors, find secrets, and kill enemies.', 'http://ericmedine.com/ShakeRattleGlow/', 'https://vimeo.com/39658566', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Programming: Eric Medine, Jessica Kim\r\nArt: Joshua Harris, Cat Sze', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 84, 21, '2012-04-02 13:45:20', '2012-04-02 13:47:49', '7271b1eece5080b9cf9944939979891f'),
(253, 'Secret Dad', 'uploads/253/game.png', 'Imagine if you had to secretly support your family via complex ventilation passages in your large industrial home?', 'You are Pete. A difficult divorce split you up from your wife and kids, but all you want to do is spend time with your family. So you hide in the ventilation ducts of your old house doing menial tasks for your family as you try to win back their love.\r\n\r\nBoth of our programmers dropped out before work even began on the game, so what you see here is the product of two people who have no experience in game creation whatsoever. We didn''t want to throw in the towel though, so we carried on anyway.', 'uploads/253/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Art by Kari Raos Clark\r\nEverything else by Cody Clark', 'CC BY', 'GameSalad', 234, 52, '2012-04-02 11:48:45', '2012-04-03 13:51:25', '08c3f0ba6467398e1043b034e111f6db'),
(254, 'Beggar Beats Baby', 'uploads/254/game.png', 'What if you could steal animation frames from other NPC’s animation cycles and give them to yourself or others to solve puzzles?', 'The game is a mad combination of snake and rock paper scissors, with generative audio and enjoyably confusing emotional associations for each character. One player & two (with fancy zooming camera)!\r\n\r\nThe player constantly moves (snake) and must time his animation cycle with a character he can beat (rps)!\r\n\r\nBeggar beats baby, baby beats bride, bride beats beggar, and Pixel beats all. Tongue firmly within cheek\r\n\r\nThe tweet was more of a jumping off point for our team, we went mad adding everything else under the sun. :D', 'http://www.mcggames.com/beggar-beats-baby/', '', 'Dundee, UK', '', 'Will Tiddy,\r\nRew Thomas,\r\nJaime Cross,\r\nPaul Andrew McGee', 'CC BY', 'Other', 128, 27, '2012-04-02 12:06:02', '2012-04-03 18:01:28', '66821bd1d08f45199f5ff175f562eb9f'),
(255, 'There Is A Monster at the End of this Game', 'uploads/255/game.png', 'What if you played a game where the enemies had their children chained to them?', 'There is a monster at the end of this game.\r\nUse the arrow keys to move and space to attack. For a different emotional experience, press "G" on the title screen. This game was coded in ActionScript3 using AdamAtomic''s Flixel engine. Warning: the gameplay video contains a full playthrough of the game.', 'http://noyb.retroremakes.com/Games/Molydeux.html', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r68gttEV1Hc', 'NYC, USA', '', 'Team: Adnan Agha, Vivian Allum, Stuart Partin, Reynaldo Vargas, Sam Zhang. \r\n\r\nAll music is from the To The Moon OST (http://freebirdgames.bandcamp.com/album/to-the-moon-ost) by Kan Gao and Laura Shigihara; no ownership is implied. The placeholder monster sprite is from Monsters Inc. for the Game Boy Advance.', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 297, 64, '2012-04-02 12:37:48', '2012-04-03 13:21:53', '9220ffe48b02d1d8364cfc15b78f9a28'),
(287, 'Babbies on a Plane', 'uploads/287/game.png', 'Game in which you must comfort children on a plane who are afraid of flying, game mechanic is similar to spinning plates.', 'Your pilot is a busy, easily angered and irresponsible man. So it''s your duty to keep the babies on the plane from crying!', 'uploads/287/game.zip', '', 'Dieburg, Germany', '', 'Sergej K., Manuel G., Adrian L. , Frieder E. \r\n\r\nContact: info@magerage.de', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 10, 3, '2012-04-03 15:09:37', '2012-04-03 16:13:51', '92a0b8e951533fc550a571c79776e176');
INSERT INTO `game` (`gameid`, `gamename`, `gamepictureurl`, `gametweet`, `gamedescription`, `gamefileurl`, `gamevideourl`, `molyjamlocation`, `teampictureurl`, `teammembers`, `gamelicense`, `gameengine`, `pageviews`, `downloads`, `createddatetime`, `lastediteddatetime`, `editid`) VALUES
(256, '#Occupy: The Card Game', 'uploads/256/game.png', 'Imagine a game in which you have to join protests to make changes to the rules within the game''s world.', '<strong>#Occupy: The Card Game</strong> is a leaderless resistance movement against unfair rules in games. Too long the 1% has been forcing us to skip turns, discard cards, and not pass go. We will raise awareness through a collective twitter feed. Though the 1% may do their best to silence us, our dedication will pass amendments to build a better game.\r\n\r\nGame rules and printable images of all the cards are included in the downloadable PDF.', 'uploads/256/game.zip', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Jeremy Dempster // @JeremyDempster<br/>\r\nJoe France // @JoeProgram<br/>\r\nEvan Pincus<br/>\r\nGreg Pincus // @gregpincus', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'None', 144, 16, '2012-04-02 13:16:26', '2012-04-02 22:04:30', '04d1c481d106738e5d6d596af2b48407'),
(257, '"Demon" Door', 'uploads/257/game.png', '"doors and windows, however,\r\nthey interest me.\r\nI mean, what if, just imagine \r\nfor a moment\r\nthat you could actually\r\ntake CONTROL of a door."\r\n\r\n- P. Molydeux, January 16, 2011', 'A physics game where you control a revolving door to spin it offensively fast, thereby flinging people across the street to destroy windows Rampage-style.  \r\n\r\nYour demon (who is possessing the door) must dodge ill-aimed flung civilians and the bullets of the police who wise up to your evil shenanigans!\r\n\r\nMade in XNA.', 'uploads/257/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/257/team.jpg', '@bengrue - Ben McGraw\r\n@disasterpeace - Rich Vreeland\r\n@vogon - Colin Bayer\r\n@zumpiez - Jeff Hutchins', 'CC BY-NC', 'XNA', 384, 56, '2012-04-02 13:20:37', '2012-04-02 13:23:52', 'a7c9984d3f9ae6d081359193ed1f3877'),
(282, 'Glorious Ending Cinematic', 'uploads/282/game.png', 'Game in which you create the end cinematic. Then you work your way from the start of the game to make a perfect connection into that ending.', 'Glorious Ending Cinematic is an adventure game with a tragic ending that must be recreated or the player suffers.\r\n\r\nLove and fear are used in the Donnie Darko sense, and are not always the obvious choice, intentionally.', 'uploads/282/game.zip', '', 'NYC, USA', '', 'Shawn Alexander Allen @anuchallenger\r\nManuel Marcano @CavalierGames', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'GameMaker', 10, 4, '2012-04-03 08:24:52', '2012-04-03 08:24:55', 'e747037a6bc4036b4609a0affd473229'),
(260, 'Goo Goo Geiger', 'uploads/260/game.png', 'Imagine carrying a radioactive baby in a pitch black environment, your baby would act as a torch. Rocking the baby intensifies the glow etc', 'You''re lost in a series of mazes, carrying a radioactive baby. If it gets too dark, shake your mouse to rock the baby and increase its glow!\r\n\r\nhttp://www.catburton.co.uk/molyjam2012/', '', '', 'London, UK', '', 'Cat Burton (@catburton) and Mark Backler (@markbackler)', 'CC BY-NC', 'Unity3D', 120, 0, '2012-04-02 14:25:51', '2012-04-02 14:25:53', '77c93f60102fb1d1cc8f483abfe81315'),
(261, 'Breaktris', 'uploads/261/game.png', 'Imagine being able to launch a missile in Battlefield and have it hit your online friend''s car in say Burnout Paradise? This is the future', 'See what happens when the worlds of Breakout and Tetris collide.\r\n\r\nThe Breakout player wins by screwing with the Tetris player and destroying their lines, forcing them to the top.\r\n\r\nThe Tetris player wins by making lines, which creates bricks on the other side, blocking the Breakout player. If the lines drop below the death line on the Breakout side, the Breakout player loses.\r\n\r\nWindows & Mac versions included.', 'uploads/261/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3McsgkVx9xM', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/261/team.png', 'Mark Cooke // @mark_cooke ///\r\nRomain Killian // @OrxProject ///\r\nvirt (we used his music... hope it''s ok! we love you!)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 246, 59, '2012-04-02 14:27:20', '2012-04-03 09:52:55', 'd494f224aa81269cacc936be4610115a'),
(262, 'Molydeuxsa', 'uploads/262/game.png', 'A survival horror game where the enemies can only be seen in mirrors? Could add more depth by having dirty mirrors that need to be cleaned? -- http://twitter.com/#!/petermolydeux/status/113286014050635776', 'http://www.johnnesky.com/molydeuxsa.html\r\nMolydeuxsa exacts revenge on Percy the window-washer. Clean the dirty windows to see her reflection, then strike her down with the sword given to you by your ancestors. ', 'http://www.johnnesky.com/molydeuxsa.html', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', 'uploads/262/team.png', 'Ashley Zeldin and John Nesky', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 52, 7, '2012-04-02 15:25:33', '2012-04-03 10:07:37', 'ca82fb6f51a3c5b9b4b752d57ea263b6'),
(263, 'Love is Blind', 'uploads/263/game.png', '"I also love the idea of playing a character who is PRETENDING to be blind, so you have to keep bumping into things to not arouse suspicion"', 'You are Frederick Delatoole and you are marrying into an aristocratic family.  You''re fiance is marrying you because she thinks you''re blind; the trouble is you''re not.  Make your way to her without arousing the suspicion of her family... you dog.', 'uploads/263/game.zip', '', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/263/team.jpg', 'Danny Manley\r\nDavid Padron\r\nDrew Smith\r\nTravis Hopkins\r\nTyrone Schieszler', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Other', 53, 13, '2012-04-02 15:26:46', '2012-04-02 15:27:26', 'e69749a69950598f5642c6677eada093'),
(264, 'Heroes Versus Holes', 'uploads/264/game.png', 'You play a hole, you must move around an environment making certain elements fall into correct targets at the right time.', '2 player game. One person plays the Djinn and makes holes for Man to fall through. Man collects lamps to get points. When Man falls through, players switch roles. Requires Love2D to run. https://love2d.org/', 'uploads/264/game.zip', 'http://www.justin.tv/molyjamto/b/313630533', 'Toronto, Canada', 'uploads/264/team.jpg', 'Darin Walsh - Graphical Art Assets; Kyle Johnston - Music; Tanner Rogalsky - Code', 'CC BY', 'None', 26, 5, '2012-04-02 15:56:15', '2012-04-02 16:15:32', 'ae8feceed9099dd27cfd0ba610cdeedd'),
(265, 'Hourglass: Countdown to destruction', 'uploads/265/game.png', 'Genre : Platformer\r\n\r\nWhat if your body is essentially a hourglass? Intense acrobatic game where you have to make sure sand is always falling and never stops', 'The player is expected to avoid running into boxes by jumping over or attaching them and then also to collect as many mayan sand artifacts to pass time faster. You begin the game on the date which your device says is the date. The player should attempt to get to Dec 21, 2012 as soon as possible without running into those boxes as it should cause them to drop sand from your hourglass body and but falling does send you into the next day; with a lower possible high score. Collision is problematic.', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/289027/MolyJam/release/WebPlayer.html', '', 'Las Vegas, USA', 'uploads/265/team.jpg', 'Gilbert Bojorquez\r\nChristopher Jensen\r\nEdd Norris (@EddNorris @2bitENT)\r\nAlexander Owens\r\nEvan Pipho\r\nDavid Rosen\r\nRyan Turney (@Ryan_Turney)\r\nNelson W Serrano', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 71, 9, '2012-04-02 15:57:42', '2012-04-03 01:12:05', 'd0943523e04336c0fe4ae7e47be1c998'),
(267, 'Super Forest Defense', 'uploads/267/game.png', 'What if you could plant seeds that grow into cover systems?', 'Grow trees to defend the earth from a meteor shower.  Trees planted close to one another will slow each other down so grab the seeds before they hit the ground and spread them out. \r\n\r\n<br/>The game is a CoronaSDK project and can only be played in the CoronaSDK Simulator, in iPhone mode.  It can be downloaded from GitHub here:  \r\n\r\n<br/>https://github.com/toastkid/super_forest_defense', '', 'http://dl.dropbox.com/u/846812/super_forest_defense/index.html', 'Brighton, UK', '', 'Max Williams & Jonny Martyr', 'CC BY-SA', 'Other', 51, 0, '2012-04-02 16:14:06', '2012-04-03 07:30:37', '0d107f8cae4129b7244f5f0cd2a51bca'),
(268, 'Last Blood: The Rambo Experience', 'uploads/268/game.png', 'I wanted that Rambo license. My idea was that Rambo is dead, you control his ghost and must locate and hug every one of his victim''s ghosts', 'You are Rambo. You are dead.', 'uploads/268/game.zip', '', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Peter Javidpour, @javidpower', 'CC BY', 'Other', 39, 12, '2012-04-02 16:21:38', '2012-04-03 13:58:28', '05fecce481d9fb3436e87ac8bf2ca514'),
(270, 'Hole Feed Love Angel', 'uploads/270/game.png', 'You are Cupid, you must find compatible partners. One arrow in each partner, connected with lasers. If any NPC touches laser, game over', 'Quote from G4''s Rob Manuel: "Grocery stores are great places to find love. In this little game, you get to play the master matchmaker with arrows as you try to pair up the couples in the store. When you hit two, they come together with a laser tether. Pick a good match and it’s instant happiness. Lock your sights on the wrong couple and they’ll dance around. If someone else hits the laser, they become apart of the love triangle. Bad, Cupid."', 'uploads/270/game.zip', 'http://youtu.be/ZFxLfuM-TfA', 'Los Angeles, USA', '', 'Charlie Parks, Danny Parks, Danny Favela, Mei Dean Francis, Nika Harper', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 10, 4, '2012-04-02 17:09:56', '2012-04-02 17:26:13', '4c84962435d61e38b2d2d384ef99340c'),
(271, 'Unbearable: OHTLTSWALTB', 'uploads/271/game.png', '<a href="https://twitter.com/#!/petermolydeux/status/94102529461334017">(Tweet)</a> \r\nYou are a bear but for some reason your oxygen comes from hugging people. Problem is that hugging people breaks their bones. #poeticgaming', 'Walk around a city as an escaped circus bear with a problem... needing hugs to breathe.  Be careful, though, as bear arms are very difficult to control.  Game is displayed simultaneously in first, second, and third person.  See the long term results of your hugging actions on the people around you.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nSource included. Playable on OS X and Windows.', 'uploads/271/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wqR5SmJLH2A', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Elizabeth Baumel @Icetigris<br>\r\nPaul Du Bois @1pld<br>\r\nChris Jurney @jurney<br>\r\nChris Remo @chrisremo<br>\r\nAdam Rickert @AdamRickert<br>\r\nPietro Righi Riva @Mello42\r\n', 'CC BY', 'Other', 33, 7, '2012-04-02 17:10:20', '2012-04-03 18:56:46', '8f32e7462cddb8a33b6cd6a37ae5d5a7'),
(272, '''Til Dusk', 'uploads/272/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'Only one pigeon bothers to notice the man on the edge of the bread factory...', 'uploads/272/game.zip', 'http://www.justin.tv/molyjamto/b/313630100', 'Toronto, Canada', 'uploads/272/team.jpg', 'Noreen Rana (art), Mike Gillis (code), Jen Costa (sound), Kyle Johnston (sound)', 'CC BY-NC', 'Other', 10, 4, '2012-04-02 17:46:27', '2012-04-03 17:59:40', '370ada874ca1f9eae8afb3924401334e'),
(274, 'Bowl or Die!', 'uploads/274/game.png', 'A mix of the Bowling survival horror tweet and the "radio active baby as the only light source". The bowling ball is your baby.', 'Bowl or Die! The survival horror bowling game made by a solo person team. FPS horror bowling in the dark!', 'http://www.yanki.jp/molyjam2012web/', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eLut--QpVhw', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Juan Rubio', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 8, 3, '2012-04-02 19:25:56', '2012-04-03 21:07:16', '6493b3860fee2c64429eb147ff8b37a0'),
(275, 'A Civilized World', 'uploads/275/game.png', 'Perhaps someone could make the game that never was? A game that lasts one second?', 'Earth is in crisis and you are but one small player. The word on the street is that nuclear war is coming. You never know when life will end in your city. How will you spend your precious time on this planet? What will be the ramifications of your choices?', 'uploads/275/game.zip', '', 'Toronto, Canada', '', 'Dale Wick - programming, design\r\nAndrew Kroepel - music\r\nDanny Glover - programming, iOS\r\nMark Ashton - art\r\n', 'CC BY', 'Other', 8, 3, '2012-04-02 21:08:34', '2012-04-02 21:15:36', 'a6054f3e58a93d6d1d8e87eb2e00fd17'),
(276, 'Tormented Soles', 'uploads/276/game.png', 'Survival Horror combined with Bowling', 'An Arduino-based bowling augmentation that lets your bowling shoes express the terror of their day-to-day. Basically, it makes your shoes scream.', '', 'http://youtu.be/JJqCSZlgKCc', 'Los Angeles, USA', 'uploads/276/team.png', 'Andrea Benavides & Anna Lotko. Special thanks to Kryptonic for his screams.', 'CC BY', 'Other', 5, 0, '2012-04-02 21:19:05', '2012-04-02 21:30:26', '478c332eae68ba19872a521809406963'),
(277, 'Arcana', 'uploads/277/game.png', 'What if you lived in a world where all guns are required to be plugged into wall sockets? Now THAT would be a tactical shooter wouldn''t it?', 'This is our multiplayer cooperative shooter entry for the Molyjam 2012. One player generates power for the other player by constantly moving so he can shoot his weapon. Of course, the power generator is helpless and both players health is linked. Luckily the power generator can cast buffs by collecting monster drops in a specific order that allow the team to become temporarily stronger.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, there are six waves and if you get too close to your gunner you''ll both explode!', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j6K1qYrtg2c&hd=1', 'Orlando, USA', 'uploads/277/team.jpg', 'Jason (Null) Spafford<br/>\r\nMichael (Harbing) Harris<br/>\r\nPhilip (Artist) Johnson<br/>\r\nJesse (Troll) Williams<br/>\r\nMichael Beecham<br/>', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'XNA', 7, 0, '2012-04-02 23:36:55', '2012-04-03 00:58:03', '14d0a39030bc3318c8c1d32875857ffd'),
(278, '10000 MPH Racecar', '', 'Racing game where you only have 2 speeds. 0MPH and 10,000 MPH. Did you just run over a little child? who knows? how does that make you feel?', 'I thought the best way to represent a Peter Molydeux racing game is by text adventure.', 'uploads/278/game.zip', '', 'Oakland / East Bay, USA', '', 'Lou Huang, Keith Nemitz (engine)', 'CC BY', 'Other', 11, 4, '2012-04-03 00:53:37', '2012-04-03 00:54:23', 'ddd98bb26c9a2392e2387df05d067fa3'),
(279, 'Orphanage Arsenal', 'uploads/279/game.png', 'You live in a little house made of guns. You need many guns to fight invaders but you also need to keep a roof on top of your many children.', 'Protect the many children in your tiny home made of guns!  Battle alien hordes!\r\n</br></br>\r\nhttp://www.renegadeinteractive.com/FinishedProjects/OrphanageArsenal/OrphanageArsenal.html', 'http://www.renegadeinteractive.com/FinishedProjects/OrphanageArsenal/OrphanageArsenal.html', '', 'Oakland / East Bay, USA', '', 'Juan Ramirez - Art (@holajuan)</br>\r\nElijah O''Rear - Programming (@EdgeOfProphecy)</br>\r\nBrandon Sheffield - Design/Art Helper (@necrosofty)</br>\r\nPatrick Miller - Design (@pattheflip)</br>\r\nEugene Marder and Donghoon Han - Music/Design</br>\r\nJason Cutler - Production Pal</br>\r\nJay Kim - Sound Effects, Music', 'CC BY-ND', 'Unity3D', 10, 3, '2012-04-03 03:07:16', '2012-04-03 16:17:31', '19869c302c39483967042ac687c3fdf2'),
(280, 'Cardboard Baby', 'uploads/280/game.png', 'You play a babysitter. You turn up, and the baby is made of cardboard. Would you stay? I want games to start asking more ethical questions.', 'An interactive fiction that explores superficiality. The reason the baby is cardboard; her parents are so two dimensional, it''s the only way the child could have turned out.\r\n\r\nYour choices determine the fate of the babysitter. How dimensional are you?', 'http://p4.hostingprod.com/@mousechief.com/molyjam/DownloadsForCardboardBaby.pdf', '', 'Oakland / East Bay, USA', '', 'Keith Nemitz (mousechief.com), \r\nLaura Michet, \r\nDan Fabulich (choiceofgames.com), \r\nSimon Carless', 'CC BY', 'Other', 10, 4, '2012-04-03 04:22:38', '2012-04-03 04:24:16', 'df665d70ead03ca6198838090d89cfba'),
(281, 'Children of the Dead', 'uploads/281/game.jpeg', 'I want to make a FPS with school children and water pistols/waterbombs/sprinklers etc in a town where the water has been contaminated', 'This is MMO TDS + Survival game.<br />\r\nYou play as a kid, and shoot using water pistol or throw water balloons.<br />\r\nOnce you get shot few times, you became zombie, and then you have to eat others or you die due of radiation that kills you within time.<br />\r\nHTML5 (canvas) - front-end.<br />\r\nC# Mono / .Net - back-end.<br />\r\nServer will be modified to satisfy Internet needs and game will be uploaded within this week.<br />\r\nWrite me: contact at maxm dot co', '', '', 'London, UK', '', '<b>Maksims Mihejevs</b> - Developer<br />\r\n<b>Robyn Nevison</b> - Art (light version)', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'None', 7, 0, '2012-04-03 05:23:08', '2012-04-03 05:28:37', '18fbd6248eea86b2d731ca4650fb160c'),
(283, 'Goodnight Molly', 'uploads/283/game.png', 'What if the pause button was a weapon? Until developers think outside the box we’re going downhill.', 'In Goodnight Molly you play as a little girl confronting her nightmares in the middle of the night. While her eyes are closed Molly''s imagination runs wild and her nightmares multiply. If Molly is feeling brave enough she can open her eyes and confront her fears, causing the nightmares to collapse upon one another.', 'http://noahw.net/goodnight-molly/', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Andrea Haid (animation)\r\nJoe Maliksi (music, sound, and UI)\r\nPeter Mohrbacher (art)\r\nRichard Shemaka (programming)\r\nDan Spaventa (design and tuning)\r\nNoah Witherspoon (programming)', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Unity3D', 10, 4, '2012-04-03 10:27:11', '2012-04-03 14:04:55', 'ed07a5e76bae4964d203dc564c4039fc'),
(284, 'inner worlds', 'uploads/284/game.png', '#157 I want to make a game where you see a tree, think ''Lets use that to get to space'' and you just can. Why does a tree HAVE to be just a tree?\r\n\r\n#535    Why can I not use that tree as a spacecraft? In the ultimate game, you should be able to do ANYTHIN', 'in a strange world simply getting food is as adventure', 'uploads/284/game.zip', '', 'Montreal, Canada', 'uploads/284/team.jpg', 'Jonathan Perreault', 'CC BY-SA', 'Unity3D', 12, 4, '2012-04-03 12:49:21', '2012-04-04 05:37:13', 'baf85aed10385af8ffd2ca595577a02c'),
(285, 'Lapin Mesquin', 'uploads/285/game.png', 'You control a mystical rabbit at a bus stop during Winter. You must find as many creative ways as possible to make people miss their buses.', 'Français:\r\nUn lapin tente de trouver des moyens de faire manquer leur autobus   des gens.\r\n\r\nOn a évidemment manquer de temps pour compléter les animations de "manquer l''autobus" (j''utilisais Game Salad pour la première fois) alors on va devoir continuer   travailler dessus.\r\n\r\n-----\r\n\r\nEnglish:\r\nA rabbit tries to make people miss their bus. We didn''t had time to include the "miss the bus" animation. It was the first time we were using Game Salad.', '', 'http://youtu.be/UgI5tvW_nl8', 'Montreal, Canada', 'uploads/285/team.jpg', 'Francis "narF" Sheridan Paré +//+ Annie Rodrigue', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'GameSalad', 6, 0, '2012-04-03 14:29:56', '2012-04-03 20:03:03', 'baae76cbba6799fd3e88086ff6c5f4f0'),
(286, 'When Doves Cry', 'uploads/286/game.png', 'You are a Pigeon who must go around the city trying to persuade business men not to jump off buildings by retrieving items from their home.', 'People are ending their lives.\r\n\r\nThey feel hopeless, and lost.\r\n\r\nOnly you can save them.\r\n\r\nPlay it here:\r\nhttp://driph.com/games/whendovescry/molyjam.html', 'http://driph.com/games/whendovescry/molyjam.html', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zsa--EgZWfE', 'Las Vegas, USA', 'uploads/286/team.jpg', 'Lance Lockwood (@lance_lockwood), Justin Scott, David Rosen (@jewishdave) and Chris Ainsworth (@driph)', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'Other', 11, 3, '2012-04-03 14:44:36', '2012-04-03 15:14:25', '95842dc29fd9481400b1023cb0cd895c'),
(289, 'Dulcis Ex Machina', 'uploads/289/game.jpg', 'Could playing as a vending machine be fun? That is my question to you young designers out there today.', 'Take as much money from the dudes as possible.  Use the jingle to keep them from leaving.  Get all their money, if they die of liver failure, that''s ok.  Includes a windows executable and an Android .apk build.', 'uploads/289/game.zip', '', 'Montreal, Canada', '', 'Christian Boutin\r\nFrancis Coulombe', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'Unity3D', 7, 3, '2012-04-03 18:44:52', '2012-04-03 18:46:28', 'e333b4497b7c364b8d04d9987a4368c8'),
(290, 'Unreliably Yours', 'uploads/290/game.png', '"A point and click adventure where you have to gain the trust of the pointer so it doesnt lie to you"', 'A graphic adventure about an overly ambitious team at Molyjam.', 'uploads/290/game.zip', '', 'Boston, USA', 'uploads/290/team.jpg', 'Stefan Chavdarov - Art;\r\n\r\nRick Cody - Music;\r\n\r\nGreg Kinneman - Design, Programming, Production;\r\n\r\nPaul Marzagalli - Writing', 'CC BY', 'Other', 6, 2, '2012-04-03 19:05:10', '2012-04-03 19:07:06', 'af63481b5b0cb8f9c231fd02f2badff7'),
(296, 'Sadventure', 'uploads/296/game.jpg', 'Imagine if Aeris as a ghost said you could be with her if you jump off this cliff, you do it and die, it''s game over. How would you feel?', 'In our game a ghost of your girlfriend asks you to join her by killing yourself.  If you decide not to all there is to do is wander around the landscape and ponder your existence without her.', 'http://mako-mako.net/sadventure.html', '', 'San Francisco, USA', '', 'Regina Mako- Art, Concept, Writing, Music\r\n<br><Br>\r\nHavilah Farnsworth- Animation, Game Design, Game Building\r\n<br><Br>\r\nRobert Iza- Additional Art', 'CC BY-NC-ND', 'None', 6, 3, '2012-04-04 00:21:40', '2012-04-04 00:25:41', 'e455c06d0a04a64f9e9fbcedcc0a8d1f'),
(294, 'Glorious Ending Cinematic', 'uploads/294/game.png', 'Game in which you create the end cinematic. Then you work your way from the start of the game to make a perfect connection into that ending.', 'Glorious Ending Cinematic game is a graphic adventure where your goal is to recreate the ending cinematic, as painful as that might seem. \r\n\r\nThe core mechanic is choosing between the vague terms Love and Fear as your verbs (shout out to Donnie Darko!). If you choose an option that will derail the cinematic, you will lose life (pink bar).\r\n\r\nIf it''s a major, irreversible choice, it may mean Game Over.', 'uploads/294/game.zip', '', 'NYC, USA', '', 'Shawn Alexander Allen @anuchallenger\r\nManuel Marcano @CavalierGames', 'CC BY-NC-SA', 'GameMaker', 6, 3, '2012-04-03 21:07:17', '2012-04-03 21:07:19', 'b0f84185e5d7712cb3b5509a21e5bf55'),
(295, 'Parlance', 'uploads/295/game.png', 'Was thinking about text adventure games. Imagine an adventure game set in a 3D world where all objects are made of text.', 'A solo four-hour jam exploring what a 3D text-based world might look like.\r\n\r\nUse arrows to move, mouse to look, and keyboard to interact.\r\n\r\nSource:  http://github.com/mstevenson/Parlance', 'uploads/295/game.zip', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=f7sFgxrf6i4', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/295/team.jpg', 'Michael Stevenson', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 12, 3, '2012-04-03 22:51:46', '2012-04-04 08:48:06', '5cffbe5693073ea010b84c7a6d008baf'),
(297, 'The Molydeuxds', 'uploads/297/game.png', 'Wife playing Farmville again. Sometimes I feel like telling her that without Populous it wouldn''t even exist. She has no idea at all...', 'Populous clone in a voxel terrain style with multiple Molydeux tweets as in-game mechanics.  You are a god, this is your sandbox, DO WHAT YOU WANT!\r\n\r\nAll of our source code and BINARY BUILDS are on:\r\nhttps://github.com/kLinus/Molydeuxds', 'http://nerdshaped.com/molydeuxds.html', 'http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DsyVFIbTRcY', 'San Francisco, USA', 'uploads/297/team.png', 'Kristopher Velez, \r\nMarc Hernandez,\r\nJakob Medlin, \r\nNeight Allen,\r\nJoseph Natoli (Music)', 'CC BY', 'Unity3D', 6, 3, '2012-04-04 12:31:34', '2012-04-04 12:35:37', '3a83f24f3cd151c61f4bef00675f8219');
